{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TSLHhQmZ4QCicwYrCcc4cz","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tproject_name: 'mahjong-game'\n3\tuser_name: 'Rchoi'\n4\tdate: '2026-03-26'\n5\tsections_completed:\n6\t  ['technology_stack', 'critical_rules', 'performance_rules', 'organization_rules', 'testing_rules', 'platform_rules', 'anti_patterns']\n7\tstatus: 'complete'\n8\trule_count: 85\n9\toptimized_for_llm: true\n10\t---\n11\t\n12\t# Project Context for AI Agents\n13\t\n14\t_This file contains critical rules and patterns that AI agents must follow when implementing game code for Mahjong Night. Focus on unobvious details that agents might otherwise miss. Read the full architecture document (`_bmad-output/game-architecture.md`) for complete context._\n15\t\n16\t---\n17\t\n18\t## Technology Stack & Versions\n19\t\n20\t**Runtime:** Node.js 22 LTS (pinned in `.nvmrc`)\n21\t**Package Manager:** pnpm (workspace monorepo)\n22\t**Monorepo:** `@mahjong-game/shared`, `@mahjong-game/client`, `@mahjong-game/server`\n23\t\n24\t### Client\n25\t- Vue 3 v3.5.31 + TypeScript (Composition API, `<script setup>` only)\n26\t- Vite v8.0.2 (Rolldown bundler)\n27\t- Pinia v3.0.4 (client-only UI state — NOT game state)\n28\t- UnoCSS v66.6.7 (presetWind4) + CSS custom properties\n29\t- VueUse v14.2.1\n30\t- Vue DnD Kit v2.2.0 (`@vue-dnd-kit/core`)\n31\t- Motion for Vue v2.1.0 (`motion-v`)\n32\t- Vue Router (minimal — `/room/:code` only)\n33\t\n34\t### Server\n35\t- Fastify v5.8.2\n36\t- ws v8.20.0\n37\t- Pino v9.x (Fastify-native logger)\n38\t- tsx (dev runtime — runs TypeScript directly, no build step)\n39\t\n40\t### Shared\n41\t- Pure TypeScript, zero runtime dependencies\n42\t- Consumed via source imports (no build step)\n43\t\n44\t### Testing\n45\t- Vitest v4.1.1 (unit/component, co-located `.test.ts` files)\n46\t- Playwright v1.58.2 (E2E in `client/e2e/`)\n47\t- CI command: `pnpm -r test` (runs all three packages)\n48\t\n49\t### Linting\n50\t- Oxlint v1.x (primary, all packages) — configured via root `.oxlintrc.json` with typescript + import plugins\n51\t- ESLint + eslint-plugin-vue (client only, supplementary for Vue template rules)\n52\t- `eslint-plugin-oxlint` disables overlapping ESLint rules\n53\t- Lint command: `pnpm lint` runs `pnpm -r lint` across all packages\n54\t\n55\t### Cut-line (Epic 6B)\n56\t- LiveKit v2.18.0 (`livekit-client`)\n57\t\n58\t### Version Constraints\n59\t- `strict: true` in all tsconfigs — no exceptions\n60\t- Vite 8 requires Node.js 20.19+ or 22.12+ (we use 22 LTS)\n61\t- VueUse v14 requires Vue v3.5+\n62\t- Pinia v3 requires Vue 3 only + TypeScript 5+\n63\t\n64\t---\n65\t\n66\t## Critical Implementation Rules\n67\t\n68\t### Top 5 Most Common Mistakes\n69\t1. **Optimistic updates** — Moving tiles before server confirms. See: Server Authority.\n70\t2. **`v-html` with user content** — XSS vector. See: Input Sanitization.\n71\t3. **Game logic in client/** — If both client and server need it, it belongs in shared/. See: shared/ Package Rules.\n72\t4. **Deep-mutating game state** — `Readonly<Ref>` is type-level only. See: State Access.\n73\t5. **Tile references by array index** — Indices shift on sort/call/discard. Use tile IDs. See: Tile References.\n74\t\n75\t### Server Authority — No Exceptions\n76\t- The server validates ALL game actions. Clients submit actions, server validates, server broadcasts new state.\n77\t- **No optimistic updates.** Client renders ONLY from `STATE_UPDATE` messages. When a player clicks \"Discard,\" the tile does not move until the server confirms. `Readonly<Ref>` on `useGameState` enforces this at the type level.\n78\t- Game state in `shared/` is mutated ONLY by action handlers on the server. Client never mutates game state.\n79\t\n80\t### Validate-Then-Mutate (Action Handlers)\n81\t- Every action handler: validate (read-only) → mutate (only if valid) → log → return `ActionResult`\n82\t- If validation fails, return `{ accepted: false, reason }` — zero mutations applied\n83\t- Never throw exceptions for game rule violations. Exceptions = bugs. Rule violations = result objects.\n84\t\n85\t### State Access — Three Tiers, Never Mixed\n86\t- **Game state:** `inject(gameStateKey)` — provided once by `RoomView`, injected by descendants. Comes from server via `useGameState` composable.\n87\t- **Component data:** Props from parent (which tile, which player)\n88\t- **Client-local state:** Pinia stores directly (`usePreferencesStore`, `useRackStore`, `useAudioStore`, `useChatStore`, `useConnectionStore`, `useHandGuidanceStore`)\n89\t- **Never** access game state via Pinia. **Never** access Pinia state via inject. **Never** import WebSocket APIs in components.\n90\t- `Readonly<Ref>` is type-level enforcement only — not a runtime freeze. Never attempt to mutate any property of the game state object, even nested ones. The server is the only source of truth.\n91\t\n92\t### shared/ Package Rules\n93\t- Zero runtime dependencies. Only `devDependencies`.\n94\t- No `console.*` — use injected `Logger` interface\n95\t- No browser APIs (`window`, `document`, `localStorage`)\n96\t- No Node.js APIs (`fs`, `process`, `Buffer`)\n97\t- Import types from specific files, not barrels (within the package)\n98\t- All game logic lives here — if both client and server need it, it belongs in shared/\n99\t\n100\t### Vue Component Rules\n101\t- Always `<script setup lang=\"ts\">` — no Options API, no `<script>` without setup\n102\t- Props typed via `defineProps<{}>()` — no runtime prop validation\n103\t- Section order: imports, props/emits, inject, composables/stores, computed, methods\n104\t- Keep components under 150 lines. Extract child components or composables if exceeding.\n105\t- UnoCSS utility classes preferred over scoped styles\n106\t\n107\t### Tile References\n108\t- Always reference tiles by ID (`bam-3-2`), never by array index\n109\t- Tile IDs are stable for the duration of a game; array indices shift on sort, call, and discard\n110\t- The pattern matching engine, Joker exchange, and all UI components use tile IDs\n111\t\n112\t### WebSocket Protocol\n113\t- JSON over WebSocket. Version field in every message.\n114\t- Three client message types: `ACTION`, `CHAT`, `REACTION`\n115\t- Chat is a SEPARATE channel from game state — never embedded in `STATE_UPDATE`\n116\t- Reactions are fire-and-forget — no storage, no replay on reconnect\n117\t- Chat history: server retains last 200 messages, sent once on connect/reconnect\n118\t- Errors sent ONLY to the offending client — never broadcast\n119\t\n120\t### Input Sanitization\n121\t- All user strings via Vue `{{ }}` interpolation — **never `v-html`**\n122\t- Chat messages: server caps at 500 chars, strips control characters\n123\t- Display names: server caps at 30 chars, strips control characters\n124\t- Reactions: must match predefined emoji allowlist\n125\t- **No DOMPurify needed for MVP.** All user content is plain text rendered via `{{ }}`. If rich text or markdown rendering is added later, add DOMPurify at that point.\n126\t\n127\t### Information Boundary\n128\t- Clients receive ONLY their own rack + publicly visible state\n129\t- Opponent rack data is NEVER transmitted\n130\t- `buildPlayerView(state, playerId)` filters before every broadcast\n131\t- The ONLY exception: `GET /api/debug/rooms/:code` (dev only, disabled in production)\n132\t\n133\t### Session Identity\n134\t- Server-generated UUID in `sessionStorage` (not `localStorage`)\n135\t- Tab-scoped: refresh preserves, tab close clears\n136\t- One active connection per token — second connection disconnects the first\n137\t- Token sent on every WebSocket connect for reconnection\n138\t\n139\t---\n140\t\n141\t## Performance Rules\n142\t\n143\t### Frame Budget\n144\t- Target: 60fps for all animations (16.6ms per frame)\n145\t- Floor: 30fps on low-end mobile with WebRTC active\n146\t- Below 30fps is a bug — file and fix as P1\n147\t- This is SVG/CSS rendering, not GPU-intensive — performance issues are likely DOM thrashing or excessive re-renders, not rendering complexity\n148\t\n149\t### Bundle Size\n150\t- Total budget: <5MB (excluding LiveKit WebRTC SDK)\n151\t- SVG tile sprite: ~200KB\n152\t- Audio assets: ~500KB\n153\t- App JS/CSS: remainder (~4MB budget)\n154\t- Before adding any new dependency, check its bundle size. No single dependency should exceed 50KB gzipped without explicit justification.\n155\t\n156\t### Load Times\n157\t- Initial load: <3s broadband, <5s 3G\n158\t- Room join to first interaction: <2s after page load\n159\t- First-visit entrance animation (2s felt fade-in) covers the initial load naturally\n160\t- Subsequent visits: near-instant with cached assets\n161\t- Vite 8's Rolldown handles code splitting automatically — don't manually configure chunks unless profiling shows a need\n162\t\n163\t### Hand Guidance Computation\n164\t- Runs client-side on every draw/discard — must complete in <100ms\n165\t- Full recompute every time — no incremental caching\n166\t- Phase 1 filtering eliminates 80-90% of hands cheaply before expensive pattern matching\n167\t- If performance degrades, optimize Phase 1 filtering first — don't add caching\n168\t\n169\t### WebSocket State Updates\n170\t- Full game state (~10-15KB JSON) broadcast to each client on every action\n171\t- At one update every few seconds with 4-5 recipients, this is trivial bandwidth\n172\t- `JSON.stringify` on 15KB objects is microseconds — don't pre-optimize serialization\n173\t- If profiling shows a bottleneck, the issue is likely in `buildPlayerView` filtering, not serialization\n174\t\n175\t### Vue Reactivity\n176\t- `useGameState` replaces the entire state ref on each `STATE_UPDATE` — this triggers re-renders in all watching components\n177\t- Use `computed` properties to derive slices of state — components only re-render when their specific slice changes\n178\t- Never deep-watch the entire game state (`watch(gameState, ..., { deep: true })`) — use specific computed refs instead\n179\t- Motion for Vue animations are hardware-accelerated — they don't compete with Vue's render cycle\n180\t\n181\t### What NOT to Optimize\n182\t- Don't object-pool tiles — there are only 152 and they're DOM elements, not canvas sprites\n183\t- Don't lazy-load the SVG sprite — it's ~200KB and should be cached on first load\n184\t- Don't debounce `STATE_UPDATE` processing — updates are infrequent (seconds apart) and must be applied immediately\n185\t- Don't web-worker the pattern matching engine — sub-millisecond computation doesn't justify the message-passing overhead\n186\t- Don't compress WebSocket messages — JSON payloads are small, compression adds latency\n187\t- Don't manually configure Vite code splitting — Rolldown handles it automatically\n188\t\n189\t---\n190\t\n191\t## Code Organization Rules\n192\t\n193\t### Package Boundaries (The One Rule That Matters Most)\n194\t- `shared/` → imported by client/ and server/. Pure TypeScript. Zero runtime deps.\n195\t- `client/` → imports shared/. Never imports server/.\n196\t- `server/` → imports shared/. Never imports client/.\n197\t- TypeScript project references enforce this at compile time. If it compiles, the boundary is intact.\n198\t\n199\t### Where Does This Code Go?\n200\t- \"Does both client and server need this?\" → `shared/`\n201\t- \"Is this a game rule or game state mutation?\" → `shared/engine/`\n202\t- \"Is this NMJL card logic?\" → `shared/card/`\n203\t- \"Is this a Vue component?\" → `client/components/{feature}/`\n204\t- \"Is this client-only reactive state?\" → `client/stores/`\n205\t- \"Is this a WebSocket/HTTP handler?\" → `server/websocket/` or `server/http/`\n206\t- \"Is this room lifecycle?\" → `server/rooms/`\n207\t- \"Is this a test helper?\" → `shared/testing/`\n208\t\n209\t### Import Rules\n210\t- Between packages: import from the barrel (`@mahjong-game/shared`)\n211\t- Within a package: import from the specific file (`../types/game-state`), never from barrel\n212\t- Shared test utilities: `import { createTestState } from '@mahjong-game/shared/testing/helpers'`\n213\t\n214\t### File Creation Checklist\n215\tWhen creating any new `.ts` file in shared/ or server/:\n216\t1. Create the file\n217\t2. Create `{filename}.test.ts` next to it\n218\t3. Write at least one test before the implementation is complete\n219\t\n220\tWhen creating any new `.vue` file:\n221\t1. Create the component\n222\t2. If it has logic beyond template binding, create `{ComponentName}.test.ts` next to it\n223\t3. If it's over 150 lines, split before committing\n224\t\n225\t### CSS Rules\n226\t- **Preset:** `presetWind4` (Tailwind v4 compatible) — modern CSS features, OKLCH colors, auto-generated theme CSS variables, built-in reset.\n227\t- **Transformers:** `transformerVariantGroup` for grouped variants (`hover:(bg-red text-white)`), `transformerDirectives` for `@apply` in scoped styles.\n228\t- UnoCSS utility classes for layout, spacing, sizing, display — in the template\n229\t- **UnoCSS shortcuts** in `uno.config.ts` for repeated patterns (button styles, card containers, tile wrappers). Don't duplicate utility combinations across components — extract to a shortcut.\n230\t- **Theme colors** registered in `uno.config.ts` theme. Wind4 auto-generates CSS variables (`--colors-felt-teal`), so define colors in the UnoCSS theme config — not in a separate `theme.css`. Use `bg-felt-teal` in templates.\n231\t- **Wind4 theme keys** differ from Wind3: `font` not `fontFamily`, `radius` not `borderRadius`, `shadow` not `boxShadow`, `breakpoint` not `breakpoints`. See preset-wind4 docs for full mapping.\n232\t- Scoped `<style>` only when a component needs complex selectors that utility classes can't express (rare). Use `@apply` via transformer-directives if combining utilities in scoped styles.\n233\t- **Never hardcode color values in components** — always reference UnoCSS theme\n234\t- Entry point: `import 'virtual:uno.css'` in `client/src/main.ts` (no separate reset import needed with Wind4)\n235\t\n236\t### Environment Variables\n237\t- Client: `VITE_` prefix required (e.g., `VITE_WS_URL`). Anything without prefix is invisible to the browser.\n238\t- Server: No prefix (e.g., `PORT`, `LOG_LEVEL`, `DEBUG_ENDPOINTS`). Never use `VITE_` for server-only values.\n239\t- Never commit `.env.local` files. `.env` files with defaults are committed. `.env.local` overrides are gitignored.\n240\t\n241\t---\n242\t\n243\t## Testing Rules\n244\t\n245\t### Test Structure\n246\t- Co-located: `foo.ts` → `foo.test.ts` in the same directory\n247\t- E2E exception: `client/e2e/*.spec.ts` (Playwright, separate from Vitest)\n248\t- CI command: `pnpm -r test` runs all three packages\n249\t- Install `@pinia/testing` as a dev dependency in client/\n250\t\n251\t### Vitest Configuration\n252\t\n253\t**Auto-reset mocks in all three vitest configs:**\n254\t```typescript\n255\t// vitest.config.ts (each package)\n256\tdefineConfig({\n257\t  test: {\n258\t    restoreMocks: true,\n259\t    clearMocks: true,\n260\t    unstubEnvs: true,\n261\t    unstubGlobals: true,\n262\t  },\n263\t})\n264\t```\n265\t\n266\t### What to Test, by Package\n267\t\n268\t**shared/ (most critical):**\n269\t- Every action handler: valid action → correct state mutation, invalid action → rejection with zero mutations\n270\t- Pattern matching engine: ALL 50+ NMJL card hands, Joker substitution at every eligible position, concealed/exposed validation\n271\t- Card data integrity: all hands parseable, no duplicates, valid group sizes, Joker eligibility consistent\n272\t- Wall generation: correct tile count (152), correct distribution, shuffle randomness with seeded PRNG\n273\t- Scoring: payment calculations for discard Mahjong, self-drawn Mahjong, wall game\n274\t\n275\t**server/:**\n276\t- Message handler: valid messages dispatched correctly, malformed messages dropped, invalid sessions rejected\n277\t- State broadcaster: player view hides opponent racks, spectator view hides all racks\n278\t- Room lifecycle: creation, join, seat assignment, cleanup triggers\n279\t- Input sanitization: chat length caps, control character stripping, emoji allowlist\n280\t- Use `vi.useFakeTimers()` for call window and grace period timer tests\n281\t\n282\t**client/:**\n283\t- Composables with lifecycle hooks or inject: use `withSetup` helper pattern\n284\t- Components: blackbox approach — test behavior (user interactions, rendered output, emitted events), not implementation details\n285\t- Pinia stores: use `setActivePinia(createPinia())` in `beforeEach` for store unit tests\n286\t- Don't test pure template rendering — if a component just maps props to template, skip the test\n287\t\n288\t### Testing Patterns\n289\t\n290\t**Blackbox component testing — test behavior, not implementation:**\n291\t```typescript\n292\t// CORRECT: Test what the user sees and does\n293\ttest('call buttons appear during call window', async () => {\n294\t  const wrapper = mount(CallButtons, {\n295\t    props: { callWindow: { status: 'open', validCalls: ['pung', 'kong'] } },\n296\t    global: { plugins: [createTestingPinia({ createSpy: vi.fn })] }\n297\t  })\n298\t\n299\t  expect(wrapper.find('[data-testid=\"call-pung\"]').exists()).toBe(true)\n300\t  await wrapper.find('[data-testid=\"call-pung\"]').trigger('click')\n301\t  expect(wrapper.emitted('call')).toBeTruthy()\n302\t})\n303\t\n304\t// WRONG: Don't test component internals\n305\t// expect(wrapper.vm.isCallWindowOpen).toBe(true)  // Never do this\n306\t```\n307\t\n308\t**Pinia store testing in components — use createTestingPinia:**\n309\t```typescript\n310\timport { createTestingPinia } from '@pinia/testing'\n311\t\n312\tconst wrapper = mount(SettingsPanel, {\n313\t  global: {\n314\t    plugins: [\n315\t      createTestingPinia({\n316\t        createSpy: vi.fn,\n317\t        initialState: { preferences: { fontSize: 'large', darkMode: 'auto' } }\n318\t      })\n319\t    ]\n320\t  }\n321\t})\n322\t```\n323\t\n324\t**Pinia store unit testing — setActivePinia:**\n325\t```typescript\n326\timport { setActivePinia, createPinia } from 'pinia'\n327\t\n328\tbeforeEach(() => { setActivePinia(createPinia()) })\n329\t\n330\ttest('defaults to auto dark mode', () => {\n331\t  const store = usePreferencesStore()\n332\t  expect(store.darkMode).toBe('auto')\n333\t})\n334\t```\n335\t\n336\t**Composable testing — withSetup helper for inject/lifecycle:**\n337\t```typescript\n338\timport { withSetup } from '@mahjong-game/shared/testing/helpers'\n339\t\n340\ttest('useHandGuidance recomputes on state change', async () => {\n341\t  const [result, app] = withSetup(\n342\t    () => useHandGuidance(),\n343\t    { provide: { [gameStateKey]: mockGameState } }\n344\t  )\n345\t  // assertions...\n346\t  app.unmount() // Always clean up\n347\t})\n348\t```\n349\t\n350\t**Async testing — always await triggers and use flushPromises:**\n351\t```typescript\n352\timport { flushPromises } from '@vue/test-utils'\n353\t\n354\tawait wrapper.find('[data-testid=\"discard-confirm\"]').trigger('click')\n355\tawait flushPromises() // Wait for WebSocket response simulation\n356\texpect(wrapper.find('[data-testid=\"call-window\"]').exists()).toBe(true)\n357\t```\n358\t\n359\t**Timer testing:**\n360\t```typescript\n361\tbeforeEach(() => { vi.useFakeTimers() })\n362\tafterEach(() => { vi.useRealTimers() })\n363\t\n364\ttest('call window expires', () => {\n365\t  const onExpire = vi.fn()\n366\t  timer.start(5000, onExpire)\n367\t  vi.advanceTimersByTime(5000)\n368\t  expect(onExpire).toHaveBeenCalledOnce()\n369\t})\n370\t```\n371\t\n372\t### What NOT to Test\n373\t- Don't mock the game engine in server tests — use the real engine with test state fixtures\n374\t- Don't test Vue component internals (`wrapper.vm.*`) — blackbox only\n375\t- Don't use snapshot tests as the only assertion — always pair with behavioral assertions\n376\t- Don't test VueUse composables — they're already tested upstream\n377\t- Don't test Pinia store getters that are trivial computed properties\n378\t- Don't write E2E tests for every interaction — focus on full game flows (join → play → Mahjong → rematch)\n379\t- Don't chain multiple `nextTick` calls — use `flushPromises` instead\n380\t\n381\t---\n382\t\n383\t## Platform & Build Rules\n384\t\n385\t### Target Browsers\n386\t- Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge — latest two versions\n387\t- iOS Safari 16+, Android Chrome\n388\t- No polyfills for legacy browsers — this covers 95%+ of the target audience\n389\t\n390\t### Mobile-Specific\n391\t- Minimum tap targets: 44px (WCAG)\n392\t- Account for mobile browser chrome (safe area insets via `env(safe-area-inset-*)`)\n393\t- Landscape recommended, portrait supported with adapted layout\n394\t- Graceful mic/camera permission prompts — guide the user, don't assume permission granted\n395\t\n396\t### Device Testing\n397\t- **Layout/viewport:** Playwright device emulation is sufficient for responsive testing\n398\t- **WebRTC (LiveKit):** MUST test on real physical iOS and Android devices — emulators can't test mic/camera permission flows or actual audio/video quality\n399\t- Don't leave mobile testing for the end — test on real devices from Epic 5A onward\n400\t\n401\t### Accessibility (Non-Negotiable)\n402\t- Semantic HTML from day one — not retrofitted\n403\t- ARIA labels on all interactive elements\n404\t- Keyboard navigation: Tab cycles zones, Arrow keys within zones, Enter confirms, Escape exits focus\n405\t- `prefers-reduced-motion`: Motion for Vue handles this natively — verify it's working, don't add manual checks\n406\t- `prefers-color-scheme`: Auto dark mode via UnoCSS `dark:` variant + manual override in settings\n407\t- High contrast and color-blind support deferred to Epic 8, but don't make design choices that block them (e.g., never rely on color alone to distinguish tile suits)\n408\t\n409\t### Build Artifacts\n410\tTwo separate deployables — never bundled together:\n411\t- **Client:** Static bundle (HTML/CSS/JS/SVG/audio) → deployable to any static host or CDN. `VITE_WS_URL` env var points to the server's WebSocket endpoint.\n412\t- **Server:** Node.js process (Fastify + ws) → deployable to any Node.js host (VPS, container, PaaS). Requires persistent processes — no serverless.\n413\t\n414\t### Build & Deploy\n415\t- Vite 8 with Rolldown handles bundling — don't configure manually unless profiling shows a need\n416\t- `import.meta.env.DEV` gates all debug features — Vite tree-shakes them from production\n417\t- No source maps in production builds (default Vite behavior)\n418\t\n419\t---\n420\t\n421\t## Critical Don't-Miss Rules\n422\t\n423\t### Anti-Patterns — Never Do These\n424\t- **Never import from server/ in client/ or vice versa.** TypeScript project references block this at compile time, but an agent might try to work around it. The shared/ package is the only bridge.\n425\t- **Never store game state in Pinia.** Game state comes from the server via `useGameState` composable and provide/inject. Pinia is exclusively for client-local UI state.\n426\t- **Never use `setTimeout` in shared/.** Shared/ is pure game logic with no runtime dependencies. Timers live in server/ (`GameTimer`) or client/ (VueUse composables).\n427\t- **Never use `Math.random()` in shared/ for game logic.** Wall shuffle must use a seeded PRNG for reproducibility and testability. `Math.random()` is non-deterministic and untestable.\n428\t- **Never send opponent rack data to clients.** `buildPlayerView` filters this before broadcast. If you're tempted to send hidden data \"for convenience,\" you're breaking the security model.\n429\t- **Never use `any` type.** TypeScript strict mode is on. Use `unknown` if the type is truly unknown, then narrow it.\n430\t- **Never put secrets in `VITE_*` env vars.** They're bundled into the client and visible to anyone.\n431\t- **Never use a singleton game engine across rooms.** Each room gets its own `createGameEngine(logger)` call with its own state object. An agent might try to create one engine and share it — this would cause rooms to corrupt each other's state.\n432\t\n433\t### Gotchas — Easy to Get Wrong\n434\t- **Tile IDs include a copy suffix.** There are 4 copies of most tiles. `bam-3` is not a valid tile ID — `bam-3-1` through `bam-3-4` are. An agent writing tile lookup code must account for the copy suffix.\n435\t- **NEWS is not a kong.** It's 4 different wind tiles (singles), not 4 identical tiles. Jokers cannot substitute. An agent implementing call validation must treat NEWS as a special group type.\n436\t- **Year digits (2-0-2-6) are singles.** Same as NEWS — they're individual tiles, not a group of identical tiles. 0 maps to Soap/White Dragon.\n437\t- **Pairs cannot be called.** A player cannot call a discard to form a pair — pairs must come from wall draws. The only exception is calling Mahjong on the final tile. An agent implementing call detection must exclude pairs.\n438\t- **Jokers cannot be discarded.** Once a Joker is in your hand, it stays. An agent implementing the discard action must validate this.\n439\t- **Exposed group identity is fixed at exposure time.** If a player exposes a \"Kong of 3-Bam\" with 2 natural tiles and 2 Jokers, the group is permanently \"Kong of 3-Bam.\" Exchanging a Joker out doesn't change the identity. This matters for Joker exchange validation.\n440\t- **Call window freeze is UX, not fairness.** In-flight calls sent before the freeze arrives at the client are still valid. The server's call buffer accepts them. Priority is always seat position, never timing.\n441\t- **Charleston blind pass timing.** During the Left pass (first Charleston) and Right pass (second Charleston), tiles must be selected BEFORE the Across pass tiles are revealed. The UI must enforce this sequence — it's not just a rule, it's a UI gating requirement.\n442\t- **`sessionStorage` vs `localStorage`.** Session tokens go in `sessionStorage` (tab-scoped). User preferences go in `localStorage` (persisted). Mixing these up breaks reconnection or preference persistence.\n443\t- **Vue `provide` must happen in setup, synchronously.** An agent can't conditionally provide game state after an async operation. `RoomView` provides immediately, even if `state` is initially null. Components check for null.\n444\t- **Always `await flushPromises()` after simulating WebSocket state updates in component tests.** Game state arrives asynchronously via WebSocket. Without flushing, assertions run against stale state — the single most common source of flaky Vue tests in this project.\n445\t\n446\t---\n447\t\n448\t## Usage Guidelines\n449\t\n450\t**For AI Agents:**\n451\t- Read this file before implementing any game code\n452\t- Follow ALL rules exactly as documented\n453\t- When in doubt, prefer the more restrictive option\n454\t- Reference the full architecture document (`_bmad-output/game-architecture.md`) for detailed context\n455\t\n456\t**For Humans:**\n457\t- Keep this file lean and focused on agent needs\n458\t- Update when technology stack changes\n459\t- Review quarterly for outdated rules\n460\t- Remove rules that become obvious over time\n461\t\n462\tLast Updated: 2026-03-26\n463\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01W7ZF8xpn2v9LuET5qhQZ2o","session_id":"e018b2a0-f3f1-40e1-98cc-69fb37f4a59e","uuid":"bca2fc92-0268-4288-993a-6719265d9ea5","timestamp":"2026-03-28T03:08:58.249Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WJ6VjvUv4yQod8uFhe9Tto","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 3A.1: Call Window — Open, Timer, Pass & Early Close\n2\t\n3\tStatus: done\n4\t\n5\t## Story\n6\t\n7\tAs a **developer**,\n8\tI want **a call window that opens after each discard with a configurable timer, allows players to pass, and closes early when all players have passed**,\n9\tSo that **other players have a fair, timed opportunity to claim each discarded tile (FR19, FR20)**.\n10\t\n11\t## Acceptance Criteria (BDD)\n12\t\n13\t1. **Call window opens after discard:**\n14\t   - **Given** a player discards a tile\n15\t   - **When** the discard action resolves\n16\t   - **Then** a call window opens with state `callWindow: { discardedTileId, discarderId, status: 'open', remainingMs, passes: [discarderId] }` and the discarder is auto-marked as passed\n17\t\n18\t2. **Timer expires with no calls:**\n19\t   - **Given** an open call window\n20\t   - **When** the configurable timer (default 5s, range 3-5s from host settings) expires with no calls\n21\t   - **Then** the call window closes (`callWindow` set to `null`), no call is resolved, and the next player in turn order draws from the wall\n22\t\n23\t3. **All players pass closes early:**\n24\t   - **Given** an open call window with 3 non-discarder players\n25\t   - **When** all 3 players dispatch `PASS_CALL`\n26\t   - **Then** the call window closes immediately without waiting for the timer\n27\t\n28\t4. **Discarder cannot call:**\n29\t   - **Given** a player who is the discarder\n30\t   - **When** they attempt to dispatch `PASS_CALL` or any call action\n31\t   - **Then** `{ accepted: false, reason: 'DISCARDER_CANNOT_CALL' }` is returned\n32\t\n33\t5. **Already passed validation:**\n34\t   - **Given** a player who already passed\n35\t   - **When** they attempt to pass again\n36\t   - **Then** `{ accepted: false, reason: 'ALREADY_PASSED' }` is returned\n37\t\n38\t6. **No window validation:**\n39\t   - **Given** no call window is open (`callWindow` is `null`)\n40\t   - **When** a player dispatches `PASS_CALL`\n41\t   - **Then** `{ accepted: false, reason: 'NO_CALL_WINDOW' }` is returned\n42\t\n43\t7. **Wrong phase validation:**\n44\t   - **Given** the game is not in `play` phase\n45\t   - **When** a player dispatches `PASS_CALL`\n46\t   - **Then** `{ accepted: false, reason: 'WRONG_PHASE' }` is returned\n47\t\n48\t8. **Call window only opens during play phase:**\n49\t   - **Given** a game not in `play` phase\n50\t   - **When** any state transition occurs\n51\t   - **Then** no call window is opened\n52\t\n53\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n54\t\n55\t- [x] Task 1: Define `CallWindowState` interface and `PassCallAction` type (AC: #1, #4, #6)\n56\t  - [x] 1.1 Add `CallWindowState` to `types/game-state.ts` — replace `callWindow: null` with `callWindow: CallWindowState | null`\n57\t  - [x] 1.2 Add `PassCallAction` to `types/actions.ts` and extend `GameAction` union\n58\t  - [x] 1.3 Add `CALL_WINDOW_OPENED` and `CALL_WINDOW_CLOSED` to `ResolvedAction` union\n59\t  - [x] 1.4 Add `PASS_CALL` to `ResolvedAction` union (for tracking who passed)\n60\t  - [x] 1.5 Add call window constants to `constants.ts`: `DEFAULT_CALL_WINDOW_MS`, `MIN_CALL_WINDOW_MS`, `MAX_CALL_WINDOW_MS`\n61\t- [x] Task 2: Implement `handlePassCall` action handler (AC: #3, #4, #5, #6, #7)\n62\t  - [x] 2.1 Create `engine/actions/call-window.ts` with `handlePassCall`\n63\t  - [x] 2.2 Follow validate-then-mutate: check phase, check callWindow exists, check callWindow.status === 'open', check not discarder, check not already passed\n64\t  - [x] 2.3 Mutate: push playerId to `callWindow.passes`\n65\t  - [x] 2.4 Early close detection: if `passes.length === 4` (all players including auto-passed discarder), close the window — set `callWindow = null`, set `turnPhase = 'draw'`, advance to next player\n66\t  - [x] 2.5 Return appropriate `ResolvedAction`\n67\t- [x] Task 3: Modify `handleDiscardTile` to open call window (AC: #1)\n68\t  - [x] 3.1 After discard mutation, instead of calling `advanceTurn(state)` unconditionally, open the call window\n69\t  - [x] 3.2 Set `state.turnPhase = 'callWindow'`\n70\t  - [x] 3.3 Set `state.callWindow = { status: 'open', discardedTile, discarderId, passes: [discarderId], calls: [], openedAt: Date.now() }`\n71\t  - [x] 3.4 Do NOT call `advanceTurn` — the call window must resolve first (next turn advancement happens when window closes)\n72\t  - [x] 3.5 Wall depletion check: if wall is empty after discard, STILL open call window (last discard can be called per GDD rules)\n73\t- [x] Task 4: Implement call window close/expiry logic (AC: #2)\n74\t  - [x] 4.1 Create `closeCallWindow(state)` helper in `call-window.ts`\n75\t  - [x] 4.2 On close: set `callWindow = null`, advance turn to next player counterclockwise from discarder, set `turnPhase = 'draw'`\n76\t  - [x] 4.3 Special case: if wall is empty AND window closes with no calls, end game as wall game\n77\t  - [x] 4.4 Timer expiry is server-side only (not in shared/) — add a note for server integration\n78\t- [x] Task 5: Register `PASS_CALL` in the game engine dispatcher (AC: all)\n79\t  - [x] 5.1 Add `PASS_CALL` case to `handleAction` switch in `game-engine.ts`\n80\t  - [x] 5.2 Ensure exhaustive check still works with new action type\n81\t- [x] Task 6: Write comprehensive tests (AC: all)\n82\t  - [x] 6.1 Create `engine/actions/call-window.test.ts`\n83\t  - [x] 6.2 Test: discard opens call window with correct initial state\n84\t  - [x] 6.3 Test: discarder is auto-passed in `callWindow.passes`\n85\t  - [x] 6.4 Test: PASS_CALL accepted for non-discarder, adds to passes\n86\t  - [x] 6.5 Test: PASS_CALL rejected for discarder → `DISCARDER_CANNOT_CALL`\n87\t  - [x] 6.6 Test: PASS_CALL rejected for already-passed player → `ALREADY_PASSED`\n88\t  - [x] 6.7 Test: PASS_CALL rejected when no call window → `NO_CALL_WINDOW`\n89\t  - [x] 6.8 Test: PASS_CALL rejected when wrong phase → `WRONG_PHASE`\n90\t  - [x] 6.9 Test: all 3 non-discarders pass → call window closes, turn advances\n91\t  - [x] 6.10 Test: partial passes (1 of 3, 2 of 3) → call window remains open\n92\t  - [x] 6.11 Test: call window close advances to next player counterclockwise from discarder\n93\t  - [x] 6.12 Test: wall empty + all pass → wall game ends\n94\t  - [x] 6.13 Test: discard no longer calls advanceTurn directly (regression)\n95\t  - [x] 6.14 Test: `closeCallWindow` resets `callWindow` to `null`\n96\t- [x] Task 7: Update barrel exports\n97\t  - [x] 7.1 Export new types from `index.ts`\n98\t  - [x] 7.2 Export `handlePassCall`, `closeCallWindow` from `index.ts`\n99\t  - [x] 7.3 Run `pnpm -r test` and `pnpm run typecheck` to verify zero regressions\n100\t\n101\t## Dev Notes\n102\t\n103\t### Architecture & Pattern Compliance\n104\t\n105\t**Validate-then-mutate pattern is mandatory.** Every action handler must follow: validate (read-only) → mutate (only if valid) → return `ActionResult`. See existing handlers `handleDrawTile` and `handleDiscardTile` for exact pattern.\n106\t\n107\t**Discriminated union results.** Follow the `{ accepted: true, resolved: ... } | { accepted: false, reason: '...' }` pattern established in Epic 2. Never throw exceptions for game rule violations.\n108\t\n109\t**Shared package rules apply.** No `console.*` (use Logger interface if needed), no browser APIs, no Node APIs, no `setTimeout`. Timer logic lives in server/, not shared/. The shared engine only tracks state — it does not manage real-time timers.\n110\t\n111\t### Critical Implementation Details\n112\t\n113\t**Discard handler modification (BREAKING CHANGE from Epic 1):**\n114\tThe current `handleDiscardTile` in `packages/shared/src/engine/actions/discard.ts` calls `advanceTurn(state)` at line 38. This MUST change:\n115\t- Remove the `advanceTurn(state)` call\n116\t- Instead, open the call window: set `turnPhase = 'callWindow'` and populate `callWindow`\n117\t- Turn advancement now happens when the call window closes (via `closeCallWindow`)\n118\t- **Wall depletion special case**: Current code at lines 41-48 ends the game on wall depletion after discard. This needs adjustment — per GDD, the last discard CAN be called. Open the call window even if the wall is empty. Only end as wall game when the call window closes with no calls AND the wall is empty.\n119\t\n120\t**This is the most important regression risk in this story.** Existing tests for discard/turn advancement will break and must be updated to account for the call window phase.\n121\t\n122\t**Call window state shape:**\n123\t```typescript\n124\tinterface CallWindowState {\n125\t  readonly status: 'open';  // Story 3A.4 adds 'frozen', Story 3A.5 adds 'confirming'\n126\t  readonly discardedTile: Tile;\n127\t  readonly discarderId: string;\n128\t  readonly passes: string[];  // Player IDs who passed (includes discarder)\n129\t  readonly calls: never[];    // Empty array — populated in Story 3A.2\n130\t  readonly openedAt: number;  // Date.now() timestamp for server timer reference\n131\t}\n132\t```\n133\t\n134\t**Why `calls: never[]`?** This story doesn't implement call actions (Story 3A.2 does). Using `never[]` prevents accidental use while reserving the field. Story 3A.2 will widen this to `CallRecord[]`.\n135\t\n136\t**Early close detection:**\n137\tAfter each `PASS_CALL`, check if `callWindow.passes.length === 4` (MAX_PLAYERS). All 4 players must be in the passes array (discarder is auto-added on open, 3 non-discarders pass manually). When all 4 have passed, call `closeCallWindow(state)`.\n138\t\n139\t**Turn advancement after close:**\n140\t`closeCallWindow` must advance to the next player counterclockwise from the **discarder** (not from `currentTurn`). Use the same seat-order logic as `advanceTurn` in `draw.ts` (line 42-53), but reference the discarder's seat. Note: in Story 3A.6, after a successful call, turn advances from the *caller's* seat — but that's a different story.\n141\t\n142\t**Timer is NOT in shared/:**\n143\tThe shared engine tracks `openedAt` so the server can compute remaining time. The actual `setTimeout` for timer expiry lives in server/ (using `GameTimer` class pattern described in architecture). When the server timer fires, it calls `closeCallWindow(state)` from shared/. This story only builds the shared/ logic — the server timer wiring is done in Epic 4A (Story 4A.5).\n144\t\n145\t### Constants to Add\n146\t\n147\t```typescript\n148\t// constants.ts\n149\texport const DEFAULT_CALL_WINDOW_MS = 5000;\n150\texport const MIN_CALL_WINDOW_MS = 3000;\n151\texport const MAX_CALL_WINDOW_MS = 5000;\n152\t```\n153\t\n154\t### New Action Type\n155\t\n156\t```typescript\n157\t// actions.ts — add to GameAction union\n158\texport interface PassCallAction {\n159\t  readonly type: \"PASS_CALL\";\n160\t  readonly playerId: string;\n161\t}\n162\t```\n163\t\n164\t### ResolvedAction Extensions\n165\t\n166\t```typescript\n167\t// game-state.ts — add to ResolvedAction union\n168\t| { readonly type: \"CALL_WINDOW_OPENED\"; readonly discarderId: string; readonly discardedTileId: string }\n169\t| { readonly type: \"CALL_WINDOW_CLOSED\"; readonly reason: 'all_passed' | 'timer_expired' }\n170\t| { readonly type: \"PASS_CALL\"; readonly playerId: string }\n171\t```\n172\t\n173\t### File Structure\n174\t\n175\t| File | Action | Purpose |\n176\t|------|--------|---------|\n177\t| `packages/shared/src/types/game-state.ts` | MODIFY | Add `CallWindowState`, update `callWindow` type, extend `ResolvedAction` |\n178\t| `packages/shared/src/types/actions.ts` | MODIFY | Add `PassCallAction`, extend `GameAction` union |\n179\t| `packages/shared/src/constants.ts` | MODIFY | Add call window timing constants |\n180\t| `packages/shared/src/engine/actions/call-window.ts` | CREATE | `handlePassCall`, `closeCallWindow` |\n181\t| `packages/shared/src/engine/actions/call-window.test.ts` | CREATE | Comprehensive test suite |\n182\t| `packages/shared/src/engine/actions/discard.ts` | MODIFY | Open call window instead of advancing turn |\n183\t| `packages/shared/src/engine/actions/discard.test.ts` | MODIFY | Update tests for call window behavior |\n184\t| `packages/shared/src/engine/game-engine.ts` | MODIFY | Add `PASS_CALL` to dispatcher switch |\n185\t| `packages/shared/src/index.ts` | MODIFY | Export new types and functions |\n186\t\n187\t### Testing Strategy\n188\t\n189\t**Framework:** Vitest (co-located tests). Use `vi.useFakeTimers()` if any `Date.now()` dependency matters.\n190\t\n191\t**Test helper usage:**\n192\t- Use `createTestState()` from `testing/helpers.ts` to get a full game state with 4 players\n193\t- Use `handleAction(state, { type: 'START_GAME', playerIds: TEST_PLAYER_IDS })` then manually progress to discard phase\n194\t- Use `handleAction(state, { type: 'DISCARD_TILE', playerId, tileId })` to trigger call window open\n195\t\n196\t**Multi-step test pattern (established in Epic 1):**\n197\t```typescript\n198\t// Setup: start game, draw, discard to trigger call window\n199\tconst state = createLobbyState();\n200\thandleAction(state, { type: 'START_GAME', playerIds: TEST_PLAYER_IDS });\n201\t// East has 14 tiles, skips draw, goes straight to discard\n202\tconst eastPlayer = getPlayerBySeat(state, 'east');\n203\tconst tileToDiscard = eastPlayer.rack[0];\n204\thandleAction(state, { type: 'DISCARD_TILE', playerId: eastPlayer.id, tileId: tileToDiscard.id });\n205\t// Now callWindow should be open\n206\texpect(state.callWindow).not.toBeNull();\n207\texpect(state.turnPhase).toBe('callWindow');\n208\t```\n209\t\n210\t**Regression tests to update:**\n211\tThe existing `discard.test.ts` tests expect `advanceTurn` to be called after discard. These must be updated to expect `turnPhase === 'callWindow'` instead. The `advanceTurn` behavior now happens on call window close.\n212\t\n213\t### Previous Story Intelligence\n214\t\n215\t**From Story 2-6 (Scoring & Payment Calculation):**\n216\t- Discriminated union result pattern works well — apply same for `CallWindowState` status and `ActionResult`\n217\t- `buildTilesForHand` in `testing/tile-builders.ts` available for building test scenarios\n218\t- TDD methodology: write red tests first, then implement\n219\t- Code review found return type improvements — consider actionable rejection reasons from the start\n220\t\n221\t**From Epic 2 Retrospective:**\n222\t- **Action item:** Extend test helpers for multi-step action sequences — `createTestState` needs to support discard → call window → pass flows. Consider adding `advanceToCallWindow(state)` test helper.\n223\t- **Action item:** Validate `vi.useFakeTimers()` works — this is the first timer-dependent story. Test `Date.now()` usage in `openedAt`.\n224\t- **Action item:** 7+ new action types coming in Epic 3A — extend `GameAction` and `ResolvedAction` unions cleanly. Plan for `PASS_CALL` now; Stories 3A.2-3A.8 will add `CALL_PUNG`, `CALL_KONG`, `CALL_QUINT`, `CALL_MAHJONG`, `CONFIRM_CALL`, `RETRACT_CALL`, etc.\n225\t\n226\t### Git Intelligence\n227\t\n228\t**Recent commit patterns:**\n229\t- Convention: `feat(shared): <description>` for features\n230\t- All changes in Epic 2 were in `packages/shared/src/`\n231\t- 375 passing tests as baseline — zero regressions expected\n232\t- Test count will grow significantly with call window tests\n233\t\n234\t**Backpressure gate:** `pnpm -r test && pnpm run typecheck` — run before marking done.\n235\t\n236\t### Cross-Story Dependencies\n237\t\n238\t**This story enables:**\n239\t- Story 3A.2 (Call Actions): Adds `CALL_PUNG`, `CALL_KONG`, `CALL_QUINT` — these will push records to `callWindow.calls` and transition status to `'frozen'`\n240\t- Story 3A.4 (Call Window Freeze): Adds `'frozen'` status to `CallWindowState` and priority resolution\n241\t- Story 3A.6 (Turn Advancement After Calls): Modifies `closeCallWindow` to advance from caller's seat instead of discarder's\n242\t- Story 4A.5 (Action/State Protocol): Wires server-side `GameTimer` to call `closeCallWindow` on timer expiry\n243\t\n244\t**This story depends on:**\n245\t- Epic 1 (done): Game state machine, turn loop, discard action, `advanceTurn`\n246\t- No dependency on Epic 2 (pattern matcher not needed)\n247\t\n248\t### Project Structure Notes\n249\t\n250\t- All changes within `packages/shared/src/` — no client or server changes\n251\t- New file `engine/actions/call-window.ts` follows existing pattern: `draw.ts`, `discard.ts`, `game-flow.ts`\n252\t- Co-located test file `engine/actions/call-window.test.ts`\n253\t- Barrel exports updated in `index.ts`\n254\t\n255\t### References\n256\t\n257\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics.md — Epic 3A, Story 3A.1]\n258\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/game-architecture.md — AR10: Server-timed call window]\n259\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/gdd.md — FR19, FR20: Call window mechanics]\n260\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ux-design-specification.md — Calling Flow UX Journey]\n261\t- [Source: _bmad-output/project-context.md — Validate-then-mutate, Server Authority, shared/ rules]\n262\t- [Source: packages/shared/src/engine/actions/discard.ts — Current discard handler to modify]\n263\t- [Source: packages/shared/src/engine/actions/draw.ts:42-53 — advanceTurn seat-order logic to reuse]\n264\t- [Source: packages/shared/src/types/game-state.ts:70 — `callWindow: null` placeholder to replace]\n265\t\n266\t## Dev Agent Record\n267\t\n268\t### Agent Model Used\n269\t\n270\tClaude Opus 4.6\n271\t\n272\t### Debug Log References\n273\t\n274\t### Completion Notes List\n275\t\n276\t- Implemented `CallWindowState` interface with `status: 'open'`, `discardedTile`, `discarderId`, `passes`, `calls: never[]`, `openedAt`\n277\t- Added `PassCallAction` to `GameAction` discriminated union and `PASS_CALL`, `CALL_WINDOW_OPENED`, `CALL_WINDOW_CLOSED` to `ResolvedAction`\n278\t- Created `handlePassCall` following validate-then-mutate pattern with 5 validation checks\n279\t- Created `closeCallWindow` with turn advancement from discarder's seat and wall depletion detection\n280\t- Modified `handleDiscardTile` to open call window instead of calling `advanceTurn` — this is a breaking change from Epic 1 requiring updates to existing tests\n281\t- Registered `PASS_CALL` in game engine dispatcher with exhaustive type check\n282\t- 16 new tests in `call-window.test.ts` covering all 8 acceptance criteria\n283\t- Updated 3 existing test files (discard.test.ts, wall-depletion.test.ts, game-engine.test.ts) and 1 client test file (TestHarness.test.ts) to account for call window phase\n284\t- Updated type test (game-state.test.ts) for new `CallWindowState | null` type\n285\t- All 391 tests pass (369 shared + 1 server + 21 client) with zero regressions\n286\t- TypeScript compilation clean across all 3 packages\n287\t- Lint clean (zero errors)\n288\t- `vi.useFakeTimers()` validated working for `Date.now()` in openedAt test\n289\t\n290\t### File List\n291\t\n292\t- packages/shared/src/types/game-state.ts (MODIFIED) — Added CallWindowState interface, updated GameState.callWindow type, extended ResolvedAction union\n293\t- packages/shared/src/types/game-state.test.ts (MODIFIED) — Updated callWindow type assertion, added CallWindowState import\n294\t- packages/shared/src/types/actions.ts (MODIFIED) — Added PassCallAction interface, extended GameAction union\n295\t- packages/shared/src/constants.ts (MODIFIED) — Added DEFAULT_CALL_WINDOW_MS, MIN_CALL_WINDOW_MS, MAX_CALL_WINDOW_MS\n296\t- packages/shared/src/engine/actions/call-window.ts (CREATED) — handlePassCall and closeCallWindow implementations\n297\t- packages/shared/src/engine/actions/call-window.test.ts (CREATED) — 15 tests covering all acceptance criteria\n298\t- packages/shared/src/engine/actions/discard.ts (MODIFIED) — Opens call window after discard instead of calling advanceTurn\n299\t- packages/shared/src/engine/actions/discard.test.ts (MODIFIED) — Updated for call window behavior\n300\t- packages/shared/src/engine/actions/wall-depletion.test.ts (MODIFIED) — Updated for call window phase in wall depletion flow\n301\t- packages/shared/src/engine/game-engine.ts (MODIFIED) — Added PASS_CALL case to handleAction dispatcher\n302\t- packages/shared/src/engine/game-engine.test.ts (MODIFIED) — Updated discard dispatch test, added PASS_CALL dispatch test\n303\t- packages/shared/src/index.ts (MODIFIED) — Exported new types and functions\n304\t- packages/client/src/components/dev/TestHarness.test.ts (MODIFIED) — Updated for call window behavior in draw, discard, and wall game tests\n305\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01W7ZF8xpn2v9LuET5qhQZ2o","session_id":"e018b2a0-f3f1-40e1-98cc-69fb37f4a59e","uuid":"951a2281-8c80-466d-8b2e-53d3a389f4fb","timestamp":"2026-03-28T03:08:58.250Z"}
