{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YCCeuX2RJtUzHikiDRM4qD","type":"tool_result","content":"528:### Epic 3A: Turn Flow & Calling\n548:**Dependencies:** Epic 3A, Epic 4A\n556:### Epic 3B: Charleston\n559:**Dependencies:** Epic 3A, Epic 5A\n564:### Epic 3C: Advanced Rules\n567:**Dependencies:** Epic 3A, Epic 5A\n633:  [Epic 3A] + [Epic 4A] ──> [Epic 5A]\n634:  Note: Epic 3A turn-flow stories can start parallel with Epic 2\n654:**Note on FR52 (Dead Joker):** Story 1.5 enforces that Jokers cannot be discarded (FR51). The complementary rule — that a discarded Joker is a dead tile no one can call (FR52) — requires the calling system to enforce. The calling-side enforcement of FR52 belongs in Epic 3A when call validation is implemented. Story 1.5 lays the state foundation (marking any hypothetically discarded Joker as uncallable) but the behavioral enforcement depends on 3A.\n1056:## Epic 3A: Turn Flow & Calling\n1326:**Note on call window sync:** Epic 3A builds the calling logic in the shared/ engine (local). This epic wires all game actions — including call window open/freeze/resolve — over the network via the Action/State protocol. Story 4A.5 explicitly covers call window message types and networked synchronization (AR10).\n1938:## Epic 3B: Charleston\n1942:**Note on TypeScript unions:** Stories in this epic extend `GameAction` and `ResolvedAction` unions with Charleston-specific types. See Epic 3A note.\n1944:**Note on TileSelectionAction reuse:** The TileSelectionAction composable built in Story 3B.4 should be retroactively applied to Epic 3A.5's call confirmation tile selection when this epic ships — refactor the 3A.5 implementation to use the shared composable.\n2120:## Epic 3C: Advanced Rules\n2126:**Note on TypeScript unions:** Stories in this epic extend `GameAction` and `ResolvedAction` unions with Joker exchange, dead hand, social override, and table talk types. See Epic 3A note.\n2526:**Note on TypeScript unions:** Stories in this epic extend `GameAction` and `ResolvedAction` unions with timeout, departure, host migration, and settings types. See Epic 3A note.\n2770:**Note on TypeScript unions:** Stories in this epic may extend `ResolvedAction` union with new UI-relevant resolved actions (e.g., `SHOW_HAND`, wall counter state changes). See Epic 3A note."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_013LARjtB1XKZ8zCa7VSrMaH","session_id":"e018b2a0-f3f1-40e1-98cc-69fb37f4a59e","uuid":"a2a584e8-5f73-4a12-a1d7-264e63552798","timestamp":"2026-03-28T03:08:59.662Z"}
