{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QQuNyy71EWXLwkfAZ8KXU3","type":"tool_result","content":"1200\t\n1201\t### Test Strategy\n1202\t\n1203\t**Co-located tests:** Test files live next to their source files (`foo.ts` -> `foo.test.ts`). Vitest config: `include: ['src/**/*.test.ts']`. Tests are discoverable, never orphaned, and move with their source during refactors.\n1204\t\n1205\t**Exception: E2E tests** live in `client/e2e/` with `.spec.ts` extension since they don't correspond to individual source files. Playwright runs these separately from Vitest.\n1206\t\n1207\t### Import Strategy\n1208\t\n1209\t**Minimal barrel exports.** Each package has ONE `index.ts` as its public API. External consumers (client/, server/) import from the barrel. Within a package, import directly from source files — never from barrels.\n1210\t\n1211\t```typescript\n1212\t// shared/src/index.ts — the single public API\n1213\texport type { GameState, GameAction, ActionResult } from './types/game-state'\n1214\texport type { NMJLCard, HandPattern } from './types/card'\n1215\texport type { Tile, TileId } from './types/tiles'\n1216\texport type { Logger } from './types/logger'\n1217\texport { createGameEngine } from './engine/game-engine'\n1218\texport { loadCard } from './card/card-loader'\n1219\texport { TILE_COUNT, MAX_PLAYERS, SEATS } from './constants'\n1220\texport { DEFAULT_CALL_WINDOW_SECONDS } from './defaults'\n1221\t\n1222\t// Within shared/, import directly — NOT from barrel:\n1223\timport { GameState } from '../types/game-state'  // CORRECT\n1224\timport { GameState } from '..'                    // WRONG\n1225\t```\n1226\t\n1227\t### SVG Tile Assets\n1228\t\n1229\t**Single SVG sprite sheet** containing all 152 tile faces as `<symbol>` elements. The `Tile.vue` component references tiles via `<use href=\"#bam-3\">`.\n1230\t\n1231\t```\n1232\ttile-assets/\n1233\t  tiles.svg    # All 152 faces: <symbol id=\"bam-1\">...</symbol>, etc.\n1234\t  tiles.css    # CSS custom properties for suit colors (theming hook)\n1235\t```\n1236\t\n1237\tOne cacheable asset, resolution-independent. Organized by category within the sprite (suited, winds, dragons, flowers, jokers).\n1238\t\n1239\t### System -> Location Mapping\n1240\t\n1241\t| System | Package | Location | Key Files |\n1242\t|---|---|---|---|\n1243\t| Game State Machine | shared | `engine/` | `game-engine.ts`, `actions/*.ts` |\n1244\t| NMJL Pattern Matching | shared | `card/` | `pattern-matcher.ts`, `hand-guidance.ts` |\n1245\t| Call Validation | shared | `engine/validation/` | `call-validation.ts`, `exposure-validation.ts` |\n1246\t| Charleston Logic | shared | `engine/actions/` | `charleston.ts` |\n1247\t| Wall & Dealing | shared | `engine/state/` | `wall.ts`, `dealing.ts` |\n1248\t| Scoring | shared | `engine/state/` | `scoring.ts` |\n1249\t| Card Data | shared | `data/cards/` | `2026.json` |\n1250\t| Test Utilities | shared | `testing/` | `helpers.ts`, `fixtures.ts` |\n1251\t| Room Management | server | `rooms/` | `room-manager.ts`, `room.ts` |\n1252\t| WebSocket Server | server | `websocket/` | `ws-server.ts`, `message-handler.ts` |\n1253\t| State Broadcasting | server | `websocket/` | `state-broadcaster.ts` |\n1254\t| HTTP API | server | `http/` | `routes.ts` |\n1255\t| Game Table UI | client | `components/game/` | `GameTable.vue`, `PlayerRack.vue` |\n1256\t| Tile Rendering | client | `components/tiles/` | `Tile.vue`, `tiles.svg` |\n1257\t| Call/Discard Actions | client | `components/actions/` | `CallButtons.vue`, `DiscardConfirm.vue` |\n1258\t| Charleston UI | client | `components/charleston/` | `CharlestonPhase.vue` |\n1259\t| NMJL Card Display | client | `components/card/` | `NMJLCard.vue`, `HandHint.vue` |\n1260\t| Chat & Social | client | `components/social/` | `ChatPanel.vue`, `ReactionBar.vue` |\n1261\t| Lobby | client | `components/lobby/` | `LobbyView.vue`, `WaitingRoom.vue` |\n1262\t| Scoreboard & Celebration | client | `components/scoreboard/` | `Scoreboard.vue`, `Celebration.vue` |\n1263\t| Settings | client | `components/settings/` | `SettingsPanel.vue`, `HostSettings.vue` |\n1264\t| Debug Tools | client | `components/dev/` | `DebugPanel.vue`, `MultiSeatControls.vue` |\n1265\t| Game State Composable | client | `composables/` | `useGameState.ts` |\n1266\t| Pinia Stores | client | `stores/` | `preferences.ts`, `rack.ts`, etc. |\n1267\t\n1268\t### Naming Conventions\n1269\t\n1270\t| Element | Convention | Example |\n1271\t|---|---|---|\n1272\t| TypeScript files | kebab-case | `game-engine.ts`, `pattern-matcher.ts` |\n1273\t| Vue components | PascalCase | `PlayerRack.vue`, `CallButtons.vue` |\n1274\t| Composables | camelCase with `use` prefix | `useGameState.ts`, `useHandGuidance.ts` |\n1275\t| Pinia stores | camelCase with `use` + `Store` suffix | `usePreferencesStore`, `useRackStore` |\n1276\t| Types/Interfaces | PascalCase | `GameState`, `HandPattern`, `TileRequirement` |\n1277\t| Constants | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `TILE_COUNT`, `MAX_PLAYERS` |\n1278\t| Functions | camelCase | `handleDiscard()`, `buildPlayerView()` |\n1279\t| CSS custom properties | kebab-case with prefix | `--color-felt-teal`, `--mood-arriving-bg` |\n1280\t| Test files | match source + `.test.ts` | `pattern-matcher.test.ts` |\n1281\t| E2E tests | descriptive + `.spec.ts` | `game-flow.spec.ts` |\n1282\t| SVG symbol IDs | kebab-case tile ID | `bam-3`, `wind-north`, `joker`, `flower-a` |\n1283\t\n1284\t### Architectural Boundaries\n1285\t\n1286\t1. **shared/ imports nothing from client/ or server/.** Enforced by TypeScript project references.\n1287\t2. **shared/ has zero runtime dependencies.** Only `devDependencies` (Vitest). The `Logger` interface is the only external-facing type — implementations injected from consumers.\n1288\t3. **client/ imports from shared/ (types + game logic).** Never imports from server/.\n1289\t4. **server/ imports from shared/ (types + game engine).** Never imports from client/.\n1290\t5. **No circular dependencies between packages.** Dependency graph: `shared <- client`, `shared <- server`. No other edges.\n1291\t6. **No barrel imports within a package.** Direct file imports only. Barrels are public API boundaries between packages.\n1292\t\n1293\t### TypeScript Project References\n1294\t\n1295\tBoundary enforcement uses TypeScript project references. `tsc --build` compiles in dependency order and prevents illegal cross-package imports at compile time.\n1296\t\n1297\t```json\n1298\t// tsconfig.base.json — shared compiler options\n1299\t{\n1300\t  \"compilerOptions\": {\n1301\t    \"strict\": true,\n1302\t    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n1303\t    \"module\": \"ESNext\",\n1304\t    \"moduleResolution\": \"bundler\",\n1305\t    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n1306\t    \"skipLibCheck\": true,\n1307\t    \"forceConsistentCasingInFileNames\": true,\n1308\t    \"resolveJsonModule\": true,\n1309\t    \"declaration\": true,\n1310\t    \"declarationMap\": true,\n1311\t    \"sourceMap\": true\n1312\t  }\n1313\t}\n1314\t\n1315\t// packages/shared/tsconfig.json\n1316\t{\n1317\t  \"extends\": \"../../tsconfig.base.json\",\n1318\t  \"compilerOptions\": { \"rootDir\": \"src\", \"outDir\": \"dist\" },\n1319\t  \"include\": [\"src\"]\n1320\t}\n1321\t\n1322\t// packages/client/tsconfig.json\n1323\t{\n1324\t  \"extends\": \"../../tsconfig.base.json\",\n1325\t  \"compilerOptions\": { \"rootDir\": \"src\", \"types\": [\"vite/client\"] },\n1326\t  \"include\": [\"src\"],\n1327\t  \"references\": [{ \"path\": \"../shared\" }]\n1328\t}\n1329\t\n1330\t// packages/server/tsconfig.json\n1331\t{\n1332\t  \"extends\": \"../../tsconfig.base.json\",\n1333\t  \"compilerOptions\": { \"rootDir\": \"src\", \"types\": [\"node\"] },\n1334\t  \"include\": [\"src\"],\n1335\t  \"references\": [{ \"path\": \"../shared\" }]\n1336\t}\n1337\t```\n1338\t\n1339\t### Test Utilities\n1340\t\n1341\tShared test helpers live in `shared/src/testing/`. These provide factories for creating game states, building specific hands, and generating tile configurations used across all three packages' test suites.\n1342\t\n1343\t```typescript\n1344\t// shared/src/testing/helpers.ts\n1345\texport function createTestState(overrides?: Partial<GameState>): GameState\n1346\texport function buildHand(tiles: string[]): Tile[]\n1347\texport function generateShuffledWall(seed?: number): Tile[]\n1348\t```\n1349\t\n1350\tServer and client tests import directly:\n1351\t```typescript\n1352\timport { createTestState, buildHand } from '@mahjong-game/shared/testing/helpers'\n1353\t```\n1354\t\n1355\tVitest coverage config excludes `testing/` from production coverage metrics.\n1356\t\n1357\t### Package Names\n1358\t\n1359\tScoped package names for the pnpm workspace:\n1360\t\n1361\t| Package | Name | Import Example |\n1362\t|---|---|---|\n1363\t| shared | `@mahjong-game/shared` | `import { createGameEngine } from '@mahjong-game/shared'` |\n1364\t| client | `@mahjong-game/client` | (not imported by other packages) |\n1365\t| server | `@mahjong-game/server` | (not imported by other packages) |\n1366\t\n1367\t### Workspace Configuration\n1368\t\n1369\t```yaml\n1370\t# pnpm-workspace.yaml\n1371\tpackages:\n1372\t  - 'packages/*'\n1373\t```\n1374\t\n1375\tEach package's `package.json` references shared via workspace protocol:\n1376\t```json\n1377\t// packages/client/package.json\n1378\t{\n1379\t  \"dependencies\": {\n1380\t    \"@mahjong-game/shared\": \"workspace:*\"\n1381\t  }\n1382\t}\n1383\t\n1384\t// packages/server/package.json\n1385\t{\n1386\t  \"dependencies\": {\n1387\t    \"@mahjong-game/shared\": \"workspace:*\"\n1388\t  }\n1389\t}\n1390\t```\n1391\t\n1392\t---\n1393\t\n1394\t## Implementation Patterns\n1395\t\n1396\tThese patterns ensure consistent implementation across all AI agents.\n1397\t\n1398\t### Novel Pattern: NMJL Pattern Matching Algorithm\n1399\t\n1400\t**Purpose:** Determine which card hands a set of tiles matches (for Mahjong validation) and which hands are still achievable (for hand guidance).\n1401\t\n1402\t**The challenge:** A player's 14 tiles must match one of ~50+ hand patterns. Each pattern uses color-group wildcards (A/B/C mapping to any suit), value wildcards (N/N+1/N+2), Joker substitution in groups of 3+, and concealed/exposed constraints. The matcher must handle all combinations efficiently.\n1403\t\n1404\t**Algorithm approach: Constraint satisfaction with backtracking**\n1405\t\n1406\tThe pattern matcher works in two phases:\n1407\t\n1408\t**Phase 1 — Filter impossible hands (fast):**\n1409\tFor each hand on the card, check basic feasibility:\n1410\t- Does the player have enough tiles in the right categories? (suited, winds, dragons, flowers)\n1411\t- Are exposed groups compatible with the hand's requirements?\n1412\t- If the hand is concealed, has the player called any tiles?\n1413\t\n1414\tThis eliminates most hands cheaply before doing expensive matching.\n1415\t\n1416\t**Phase 2 — Attempt assignment (per surviving hand):**\n1417\tFor each remaining hand pattern, try to assign the player's tiles to the pattern's groups:\n1418\t\n1419\t```typescript\n1420\tfunction matchHand(tiles: Tile[], exposed: ExposedGroup[], pattern: HandPattern): MatchResult | null {\n1421\t  // 1. Build available tile pool (rack tiles + exposed groups)\n1422\t  const pool = buildTilePool(tiles, exposed)\n1423\t\n1424\t  // 2. Determine color-group assignments\n1425\t  //    If pattern uses colors A, B, C — try all suit permutations\n1426\t  //    e.g., A=Bam,B=Crak,C=Dot then A=Bam,B=Dot,C=Crak, etc.\n1427\t  const suitPermutations = getSuitPermutations(pattern)\n1428\t\n1429\t  for (const suitMapping of suitPermutations) {\n1430\t    // 3. Determine value wildcard assignments\n1431\t    //    If pattern uses N, try N=1 through N=9 (bounded by N+offset <= 9)\n1432\t    const valueRanges = getValueRanges(pattern)\n1433\t\n1434\t    for (const valueMapping of valueRanges) {\n1435\t      // 4. Resolve all tile requirements to concrete tiles\n1436\t      const concretePattern = resolvePattern(pattern, suitMapping, valueMapping)\n1437\t\n1438\t      // 5. Attempt to fill each group from the pool\n1439\t      //    Jokers can substitute in groups of 3+\n1440\t      //    Pairs and singles must be exact matches\n1441\t      const result = tryFillGroups(pool, concretePattern)\n1442\t\n1443\t      if (result.success) {\n1444\t        // 6. Validate concealed/exposed constraints\n1445\t        if (validateExposureConstraints(result, exposed, pattern)) {\n1446\t          return result\n1447\t        }\n1448\t      }\n1449\t    }\n1450\t  }\n1451\t\n1452\t  return null // No valid assignment found\n1453\t}\n1454\t```\n1455\t\n1456\t**Joker allocation:** When filling groups from the tile pool, Jokers can substitute for any tile in groups of 3+. The matcher must find the optimal distribution of available Jokers (0-8) across groups. This is solved by exhaustive search — try all valid Joker distributions across the hand's groups. With max 8 Jokers across ~5 groups, the combinatorial space is bounded and small enough for brute force. No optimization or heuristic needed.\n1457\t\n1458\t**Performance considerations:**\n1459\t- Phase 1 filtering eliminates 80-90% of hands before expensive matching\n1460\t- Suit permutations: at most 6 (3! for three-suit hands), usually fewer\n1461\t- Value ranges: at most 7 (N=1..7 for N+2 patterns), usually fewer\n1462\t- Total worst case per hand: ~42 attempts (6 suits x 7 values). With ~10 hands surviving Phase 1 filtering, that's ~420 attempts — trivial for modern hardware\n1463\t- Hand guidance runs this on every draw/discard. At sub-millisecond per attempt, the full computation is well under the 100ms target\n1464\t\n1465\t**Hand guidance — full recompute:** Hand guidance runs the full matching algorithm from scratch on every draw/discard. No incremental state, no caching of previous results. The algorithm is fast enough (sub-millisecond total) that incremental computation would add cache invalidation complexity for an invisible performance gain. Stateless recomputation eliminates a class of bugs (stale cache after Joker exchange, call, or Charleston pass).\n1466\t\n1467\t**For hand guidance (closeness ranking):**\n1468\tSame algorithm but instead of requiring all groups filled, count how many tiles are missing:\n1469\t\n1470\t```typescript\n1471\tfunction handCloseness(tiles: Tile[], exposed: ExposedGroup[], pattern: HandPattern): number {\n1472\t  // Returns minimum tiles needed to complete this hand (0 = valid Mahjong)\n1473\t  // Uses the same assignment logic but tracks unfilled slots\n1474\t  // Best result across all suit/value permutations wins\n1475\t}\n1476\t```\n1477\t\n1478\tRank all hands by closeness. Display on the NMJL card: 0 = Mahjong, 1-3 = highlighted, 4+ = faded, impossible = hidden.\n1479\t\n1480\t### Standard Patterns\n1481\t\n1482\t#### Action Handler Template\n1483\t\n1484\tEvery action handler in `shared/engine/actions/` follows this exact structure:\n1485\t\n1486\t```typescript\n1487\t// shared/engine/actions/discard.ts\n1488\timport type { GameState, DiscardAction, ActionResult } from '../../types'\n1489\timport type { Logger } from '../../types/logger'\n1490\t\n1491\texport function handleDiscard(\n1492\t  state: GameState,\n1493\t  action: DiscardAction,\n1494\t  logger: Logger\n1495\t): ActionResult {\n1496\t  // -- 1. VALIDATE (read-only) --\n1497\t  if (state.gamePhase !== 'play') {\n1498\t    return { accepted: false, reason: 'WRONG_PHASE' }\n1499\t  }\n1500\t  if (state.currentTurn !== action.playerId) {\n1501\t    return { accepted: false, reason: 'NOT_YOUR_TURN' }\n1502\t  }\n1503\t  if (state.turnState !== 'discard') {\n1504\t    return { accepted: false, reason: 'MUST_DRAW_FIRST' }\n1505\t  }\n1506\t  const player = state.players[action.playerId]\n1507\t  const tileIndex = player.rack.findIndex(t => t.id === action.tileId)\n1508\t  if (tileIndex === -1) {\n1509\t    return { accepted: false, reason: 'TILE_NOT_IN_RACK' }\n1510\t  }\n1511\t\n1512\t  // -- 2. MUTATE (only if all validation passed) --\n1513\t  const [tile] = player.rack.splice(tileIndex, 1)\n1514\t  player.discardPool.push(tile)\n1515\t  state.lastDiscard = { tile, discarderId: action.playerId }\n1516\t  state.turnState = 'callWindow'\n1517\t  state.callWindow = {\n1518\t    status: 'open',\n1519\t    discard: tile,\n1520\t    discarderId: action.playerId,\n1521\t    calls: [],\n1522\t    passes: [action.playerId],\n1523\t    expiresAt: Date.now() + (state.settings.callWindowSeconds * 1000)\n1524\t  }\n1525\t\n1526\t  // -- 3. LOG --\n1527\t  logger.debug({ playerId: action.playerId, tileId: tile.id }, 'Tile discarded')\n1528\t\n1529\t  // -- 4. RETURN RESULT --\n1530\t  return {\n1531\t    accepted: true,\n1532\t    resolved: {\n1533\t      type: 'DISCARD_TILE',\n1534\t      playerId: action.playerId,\n1535\t      tile\n1536\t    }\n1537\t  }\n1538\t}\n1539\t```\n1540\t\n1541\t**Rules:**\n1542\t- Sections always in this order: validate, mutate, log, return\n1543\t- All validation before any mutation — no exceptions\n1544\t- Logger injected, not imported\n1545\t- Return typed `ActionResult` always\n1546\t\n1547\t#### Vue Component Pattern\n1548\t\n1549\tComponents follow these conventions:\n1550\t\n1551\t```vue\n1552\t<!-- components/game/DiscardPool.vue -->\n1553\t<script setup lang=\"ts\">\n1554\t// 1. Imports\n1555\timport { computed } from 'vue'\n1556\timport type { Tile } from '@mahjong-game/shared'\n1557\timport TileComponent from '../tiles/Tile.vue'\n1558\t\n1559\t// 2. Props and emits\n1560\tconst props = defineProps<{\n1561\t  tiles: Tile[]\n1562\t  playerId: string\n1563\t  isCurrentPlayer: boolean\n1564\t}>()\n1565\t\n1566\t// 3. Composables and stores (if needed)\n1567\t// const audioStore = useAudioStore()\n1568\t\n1569\t// 4. Computed properties\n1570\tconst rows = computed(() => {\n1571\t  const result: Tile[][] = []\n1572\t  for (let i = 0; i < props.tiles.length; i += 6) {\n1573\t    result.push(props.tiles.slice(i, i + 6))\n1574\t  }\n1575\t  return result\n1576\t})\n1577\t\n1578\t// 5. Methods (if needed)\n1579\t</script>\n1580\t\n1581\t<template>\n1582\t  <div class=\"discard-pool\" :class=\"{ 'is-current': isCurrentPlayer }\">\n1583\t    <div v-for=\"(row, i) in rows\" :key=\"i\" class=\"discard-row\">\n1584\t      <TileComponent\n1585\t        v-for=\"tile in row\"\n1586\t        :key=\"tile.id\"\n1587\t        :tile=\"tile\"\n1588\t        :size=\"'small'\"\n1589\t      />\n1590\t    </div>\n1591\t  </div>\n1592\t</template>\n1593\t```\n1594\t\n1595\t#### Injection Keys\n1596\t\n1597\tAll provide/inject uses typed `InjectionKey<T>` for compile-time safety. Keys defined in a single file:\n1598\t\n1599\t```typescript\n1600\t// client/src/injection-keys.ts\n1601\timport type { InjectionKey } from 'vue'\n1602\timport type { GameStateReturn } from './composables/useGameState'\n1603\t\n1604\texport const gameStateKey: InjectionKey<GameStateReturn> = Symbol('gameState')\n1605\t```\n1606\t\n1607\t#### State Access Conventions\n1608\t\n1609\tGame state flows through Vue's provide/inject to avoid deep prop drilling:\n1610\t\n1611\t```typescript\n1612\t// views/RoomView.vue — the single provider\n1613\timport { provide } from 'vue'\n1614\timport { useGameState } from '../composables/useGameState'\n1615\timport { gameStateKey } from '../injection-keys'\n1616\t\n1617\tconst gameState = useGameState(roomCode)\n1618\tprovide(gameStateKey, gameState)\n1619\t```\n1620\t\n1621\t```typescript\n1622\t// Any descendant component — inject game state\n1623\timport { inject } from 'vue'\n1624\timport { gameStateKey } from '../injection-keys'\n1625\t\n1626\tconst gameState = inject(gameStateKey)!\n1627\t```\n1628\t\n1629\t| Data | Access Method | Example |\n1630\t|---|---|---|\n1631\t| Game state (server-authoritative) | `inject(gameStateKey)` — provided by `RoomView` | Current turn, racks, discard pools, scores |\n1632\t| Component-specific data | Props from parent | Which tile to render, which player's area |\n1633\t| Client-local state | Direct Pinia store access | `usePreferencesStore()`, `useRackStore()` |\n1634\t\n1635\t**Component rules:**\n1636\t- Always `<script setup lang=\"ts\">` — no Options API\n1637\t- Props typed via `defineProps<{}>()` — no runtime prop validation\n1638\t- Section order in `<script setup>`: imports, props/emits, inject, composables/stores, computed, methods\n1639\t- Game state via inject, component-specific data via props, client state via Pinia\n1640\t- Template before style, UnoCSS utility classes preferred\n1641\t- Keep components under ~150 lines — extract child components or composables if exceeding\n1642\t\n1643\t#### useGameState Contract\n1644\t\n1645\tThe `useGameState` composable is the contract between the WebSocket connection and every component:\n1646\t\n1647\t```typescript\n1648\t// client/src/composables/useGameState.ts\n1649\tinterface GameStateReturn {\n1650\t  // Reactive state from server — read-only, replaced on each STATE_UPDATE\n1651\t  state: Readonly<Ref<PlayerGameView | null>>\n1652\t  resolvedAction: Readonly<Ref<ResolvedAction | null>>\n1653\t\n1654\t  // Connection status\n1655\t  connected: Readonly<Ref<boolean>>\n1656\t  reconnecting: Readonly<Ref<boolean>>\n1657\t\n1658\t  // Send game actions to server — fire and forget\n1659\t  dispatch: (action: GameAction) => void\n1660\t\n1661\t  // Separate chat/reaction channel\n1662\t  sendChat: (text: string) => void\n1663\t  sendReaction: (emoji: string) => void\n1664\t}\n1665\t```\n1666\t\n1667\t**Design rules:**\n1668\t- `state` is `Readonly<Ref>` — components read, never mutate. Enforces no-optimistic-updates at the type level.\n1669\t- `dispatch` is synchronous fire-and-forget — not async, no return value. The server's response comes as the next `STATE_UPDATE` which replaces `state`.\n1670\t- `null` state means not yet connected. Components gate rendering on `state !== null`.\n1671\t- Chat and reactions are separate methods matching the separate WebSocket message channels (Decision 2).\n1672\t\n1673\t#### WebSocket Message Handler Pattern\n1674\t\n1675\tServer-side pattern for processing incoming WebSocket messages:\n1676\t\n1677\t```typescript\n1678\t// server/src/websocket/message-handler.ts\n1679\timport type { ClientMessage, ActionMessage, ChatMessage } from '@mahjong-game/shared'\n1680\timport type { Logger } from 'pino'\n1681\t\n1682\texport function createMessageHandler(roomManager: RoomManager, logger: Logger) {\n1683\t  return function handleMessage(ws: WebSocket, raw: string, token: string) {\n1684\t    // 1. Parse\n1685\t    let message: ClientMessage\n1686\t    try {\n1687\t      message = JSON.parse(raw)\n1688\t    } catch {\n1689\t      logger.warn({ token }, 'Malformed WebSocket message — dropped')\n1690\t      return\n1691\t    }\n1692\t\n1693\t    // 2. Validate structure\n1694\t    if (!message.version || !message.type) {\n1695\t      logger.warn({ token, message }, 'Invalid message structure — dropped')\n1696\t      return\n1697\t    }\n1698\t\n1699\t    // 3. Resolve room and player\n1700\t    const session = roomManager.getSession(token)\n1701\t    if (!session) {\n1702\t      sendError(ws, 'INVALID_SESSION', 'Session not found')\n1703\t      return\n1704\t    }\n1705\t\n1706\t    // 4. Dispatch by message type\n1707\t    switch (message.type) {\n1708\t      case 'ACTION':\n1709\t        handleGameAction(session, message as ActionMessage, logger)\n1710\t        break\n1711\t      case 'CHAT':\n1712\t        handleChat(session, message as ChatMessage, logger)\n1713\t        break\n1714\t      case 'REACTION':\n1715\t        handleReaction(session, message, logger)\n1716\t        break\n1717\t      default:\n1718\t        logger.warn({ token, type: message.type }, 'Unknown message type — dropped')\n1719\t    }\n1720\t  }\n1721\t}\n1722\t\n1723\tfunction handleGameAction(session: PlayerSession, message: ActionMessage, logger: Logger) {\n1724\t  const { room, playerId } = session\n1725\t  // Always use session-authenticated playerId — never trust client-provided value\n1726\t  const result = room.engine.handleAction(room.state, { ...message.action, playerId })\n1727\t\n1728\t  if (result.accepted) {\n1729\t    room.broadcastState(result.resolved)\n1730\t  } else {\n1731\t    sendError(session.ws, 'INVALID_ACTION', result.reason, message.action.type)\n1732\t  }\n1733\t}\n1734\t```\n1735\t\n1736\t**Rules:**\n1737\t- Parse -> validate structure -> resolve session -> dispatch. Always this order.\n1738\t- Malformed messages logged and dropped — never crash\n1739\t- Game actions go through the shared engine — server never mutates state directly\n1740\t- Errors sent only to the offending client\n1741\t- State broadcast after every accepted action\n1742\t\n1743\t#### State Broadcasting Pattern\n1744\t\n1745\t```typescript\n1746\t// server/src/websocket/state-broadcaster.ts\n1747\texport function broadcastState(room: Room, resolvedAction?: ResolvedAction) {\n1748\t  for (const [playerId, session] of room.sessions) {\n1749\t    if (session.ws.readyState !== WebSocket.OPEN) continue  // skip closed/closing connections\n1750\t    const view = buildPlayerView(room.state, playerId)\n1751\t    const message: StateUpdate = {\n1752\t      version: 1,\n1753\t      type: 'STATE_UPDATE',\n1754\t      state: view,\n1755\t      resolvedAction\n1756\t    }\n1757\t    session.ws.send(JSON.stringify(message))\n1758\t  }\n1759\t\n1760\t  for (const session of room.spectators) {\n1761\t    if (session.ws.readyState !== WebSocket.OPEN) continue\n1762\t    const view = buildSpectatorView(room.state)\n1763\t    const message: StateUpdate = {\n1764\t      version: 1,\n1765\t      type: 'STATE_UPDATE',\n1766\t      state: view,\n1767\t      resolvedAction\n1768\t    }\n1769\t    session.ws.send(JSON.stringify(message))\n1770\t  }\n1771\t}\n1772\t```\n1773\t\n1774\t#### Timer Pattern\n1775\t\n1776\t**Client-side: VueUse composables.** No custom timer code on the client.\n1777\t\n1778\t```typescript\n1779\timport { useTimeoutFn, useIntervalFn } from '@vueuse/core'\n1780\t\n1781\t// Call window countdown display\n1782\tconst { start: startCountdown, stop: stopCountdown } = useIntervalFn(() => {\n1783\t  remainingSeconds.value = Math.max(0, remainingSeconds.value - 1)\n1784\t}, 1000, { immediate: false })\n1785\t\n1786\t// Grace period UI indicator\n1787\tconst { start: startGrace, stop: cancelGrace } = useTimeoutFn(() => {\n1788\t  showReconnectingMessage.value = false\n1789\t  showDisconnectedMessage.value = true\n1790\t}, gracePeriodMs, { immediate: false })\n1791\t```\n1792\t\n1793\t**Server-side: Thin GameTimer wrapper** around `setTimeout` with cancel and room-scoped cleanup.\n1794\t\n1795\t```typescript\n1796\t// server/src/utils/timer.ts\n1797\texport class GameTimer {\n1798\t  private handle: NodeJS.Timeout | null = null\n1799\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01FRy1xtdzjFuzxBLyNh6fGL","session_id":"e018b2a0-f3f1-40e1-98cc-69fb37f4a59e","uuid":"9f042dc7-277f-4283-a0a8-0e44a2853689","timestamp":"2026-03-28T03:09:10.997Z"}
