{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LbypBZhsvuV5LrSXJnWhN3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01RnrapY4F3q6u62ib5ASnkC","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/rchoi/Personal/mahjong-game/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/game-architecture.md","offset":1800,"limit":600},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8608,"cache_read_input_tokens":33945,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8608,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":35,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01FRy1xtdzjFuzxBLyNh6fGL","session_id":"e018b2a0-f3f1-40e1-98cc-69fb37f4a59e","uuid":"572793ce-2231-405f-b141-bd4260fe90f1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RnrapY4F3q6u62ib5ASnkC","type":"tool_result","content":"1800\t  start(ms: number, onExpire: () => void): void {\n1801\t    this.cancel()\n1802\t    this.handle = setTimeout(onExpire, ms)\n1803\t  }\n1804\t\n1805\t  cancel(): void {\n1806\t    if (this.handle) {\n1807\t      clearTimeout(this.handle)\n1808\t      this.handle = null\n1809\t    }\n1810\t  }\n1811\t\n1812\t  get active(): boolean {\n1813\t    return this.handle !== null\n1814\t  }\n1815\t}\n1816\t```\n1817\t\n1818\tEach room holds its own timer instances (call window timer, grace period timer, cleanup timer). Room destruction cancels all timers. Testable by mocking `setTimeout` in Vitest.\n1819\t\n1820\t### Consistency Rules\n1821\t\n1822\t| Pattern | Convention | Enforcement |\n1823\t|---|---|---|\n1824\t| Action handlers | Validate -> mutate -> log -> return | Code review, template in architecture doc |\n1825\t| Vue components | `<script setup lang=\"ts\">`, props typed via generics | TypeScript strict mode, Oxlint |\n1826\t| State access (game) | Via `inject(gameStateKey)` — never direct WebSocket | Architecture boundary — no WebSocket API in components |\n1827\t| State access (UI) | Via Pinia stores — `usePreferencesStore`, `useRackStore`, etc. | Pinia as single source for client-local state |\n1828\t| Props vs. inject vs. stores | Game state via inject. Component data via props. Client state via stores. | Architecture doc, code review |\n1829\t| Error responses | `ServerError` to offending client only — never broadcast | Message handler pattern |\n1830\t| Logging | Pino via injection (shared/), direct Pino (server/client) | Logger interface in shared/, no `console.*` in shared/ |\n1831\t| No optimistic updates | Client renders ONLY from STATE_UPDATE — never local prediction | Architecture hard rule, `Readonly<Ref>` enforcement |\n1832\t| Input sanitization | All user strings via `{{ }}` — never `v-html` | eslint-plugin-vue `vue/no-v-html` set to error |\n1833\t| Tile references | By tile ID (`bam-3-2`) — never by index or object reference | Tile ID system (Cross-cutting) |\n1834\t| Linting | Oxlint (primary, all packages via root `.oxlintrc.json`) + ESLint with eslint-plugin-vue (client only) | CI runs both in client; eslint-plugin-oxlint prevents duplicate rules; server/shared use oxlint only |\n1835\t| No v-html | eslint-plugin-vue `vue/no-v-html` rule set to error | Blocks any use of v-html without explicit disable comment |\n1836\t\n1837\t---\n1838\t\n1839\t## Architecture Validation\n1840\t\n1841\t### Validation Summary\n1842\t\n1843\t| Check | Result | Notes |\n1844\t|---|---|---|\n1845\t| Decision Compatibility | PASS | All stack choices compatible, no conflicts between decisions |\n1846\t| GDD Coverage | PASS | All 11 core systems and all technical requirements addressed |\n1847\t| Pattern Completeness | PASS | 10 scenarios covered with concrete code examples |\n1848\t| Epic Mapping | PASS | All 13 epics mapped to locations and patterns |\n1849\t| Document Completeness | PASS | All required sections present, no placeholders |\n1850\t\n1851\t### Coverage Report\n1852\t\n1853\t- **Systems Covered:** 11/11\n1854\t- **Patterns Defined:** 10 (1 novel + 9 standard)\n1855\t- **Decisions Made:** 7 critical/important (6 deferred with rationale)\n1856\t- **Consistency Rules:** 12\n1857\t\n1858\t### Document Quality Score\n1859\t\n1860\t- **Architecture Completeness:** Complete\n1861\t- **Version Specificity:** All Verified (web search verified 2026-03-25)\n1862\t- **Pattern Clarity:** Crystal Clear (concrete TypeScript examples for every pattern)\n1863\t- **AI Agent Readiness:** Ready\n1864\t\n1865\t### Validation Date\n1866\t\n1867\t2026-03-26\n1868\t\n1869\t---\n1870\t\n1871\t## Development Environment\n1872\t\n1873\t### Prerequisites\n1874\t\n1875\t- **Node.js 22 LTS** (pinned via `.nvmrc`)\n1876\t- **pnpm** (latest — `corepack enable && corepack prepare pnpm@latest --activate`)\n1877\t- **Git**\n1878\t- **Modern browser** (Chrome/Firefox/Safari/Edge for development and testing)\n1879\t\n1880\t### Setup Commands\n1881\t\n1882\t```bash\n1883\t# Initialize monorepo\n1884\tmkdir mahjong-game && cd mahjong-game\n1885\tgit init\n1886\techo \"22\" > .nvmrc\n1887\tnvm use\n1888\tcorepack enable\n1889\tpnpm init\n1890\t\n1891\t# Create workspace structure\n1892\tmkdir -p packages/shared/src packages/client/src packages/server/src\n1893\techo 'packages:\\n  - \"packages/*\"' > pnpm-workspace.yaml\n1894\t\n1895\t# Install shared dependencies\n1896\tpnpm --filter @mahjong-game/shared add -D vitest typescript\n1897\tpnpm --filter @mahjong-game/client add vue vue-router pinia @vueuse/core motion-v @vue-dnd-kit/core\n1898\tpnpm --filter @mahjong-game/client add -D vite @vitejs/plugin-vue unocss vitest typescript eslint eslint-plugin-vue\n1899\tpnpm add -Dw oxlint eslint-plugin-oxlint @typescript-eslint/parser\n1900\tpnpm --filter @mahjong-game/server add fastify ws pino\n1901\tpnpm --filter @mahjong-game/server add -D tsx vitest typescript @types/ws @types/node\n1902\t\n1903\t# Verify\n1904\tpnpm -r test\n1905\t```\n1906\t\n1907\t### First Steps\n1908\t\n1909\t1. Initialize the monorepo with `pnpm-workspace.yaml` and all three `package.json` files\n1910\t2. Set up `tsconfig.base.json` with `strict: true` and package-level tsconfigs with project references\n1911\t3. Create `shared/src/types/` with initial type definitions (GameState, GameAction, Tile)\n1912\t4. Create `shared/src/constants.ts` and `shared/src/defaults.ts`\n1913\t5. Build the tile set definition and wall generation (Epic 1, Story 1)\n1914\t\n1915\t### AI Tooling\n1916\t\n1917\tNo engine-specific MCP servers selected. Context7 is already available for documentation lookup. Playwright MCP can be added for E2E test development when needed.\n1918\t\n1919\t---\n1920\t\n1921\t## Document Information\n1922\t\n1923\t**Document:** Mahjong Night - Game Architecture\n1924\t**Version:** 1.0\n1925\t**Created:** 2026-03-25\n1926\t**Author:** Rchoi\n1927\t**Status:** Complete\n1928\t\n1929\t### Change Log\n1930\t\n1931\t| Version | Date | Changes |\n1932\t|---------|------|---------|\n1933\t| 1.0 | 2026-03-26 | Initial architecture complete |\n1934\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01FRy1xtdzjFuzxBLyNh6fGL","session_id":"e018b2a0-f3f1-40e1-98cc-69fb37f4a59e","uuid":"027d1518-426d-4ca6-a886-64477a122ebb","timestamp":"2026-03-28T03:09:16.336Z"}
