{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EYtCFSxDAtLkxfVg8xqi5G","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a complete summary of the current state of the codebase across all five areas.\n\n---\n\n## 1. GameAction and ResolvedAction Types\n\n**File:** `/Users/rchoi/Personal/mahjong-game/packages/shared/src/types/actions.ts`\n\n`GameAction` is a discriminated union of four action interfaces:\n\n```ts\nexport type GameAction = StartGameAction | DrawTileAction | DiscardTileAction | PassCallAction;\n```\n\n- `START_GAME` — `{ playerIds: string[], seed?: number }`\n- `DRAW_TILE` — `{ playerId: string }`\n- `DISCARD_TILE` — `{ playerId: string, tileId: string }`\n- `PASS_CALL` — `{ playerId: string }`\n\n**File:** `/Users/rchoi/Personal/mahjong-game/packages/shared/src/types/game-state.ts` (lines 93–104)\n\n`ResolvedAction` is a discriminated union embedded in `ActionResult`:\n\n```ts\nexport type ResolvedAction =\n  | { readonly type: \"GAME_STARTED\" }\n  | { readonly type: \"DRAW_TILE\"; readonly playerId: string }\n  | { readonly type: \"DISCARD_TILE\"; readonly playerId: string; readonly tileId: string }\n  | { readonly type: \"WALL_GAME\" }\n  | { readonly type: \"CALL_WINDOW_OPENED\"; readonly discarderId: string; readonly discardedTileId: string }\n  | { readonly type: \"CALL_WINDOW_CLOSED\"; readonly reason: \"all_passed\" | \"timer_expired\" }\n  | { readonly type: \"PASS_CALL\"; readonly playerId: string };\n```\n\nNote: `CALL_WINDOW_OPENED` exists as a type variant but is not currently emitted by any handler — the discard handler returns `DISCARD_TILE` and sets `callWindow` as a side effect without emitting a separate resolved event.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Call-Related Code (Pung, Kong, Quint, Call Window)\n\nThere are no pung/kong/quint action handlers yet. Only the call window infrastructure (story 3a-1) exists:\n\n**`CallWindowState` interface** (`game-state.ts`, lines 62–69):\n```ts\nexport interface CallWindowState {\n  readonly status: \"open\";\n  readonly discardedTile: Tile;\n  readonly discarderId: string;\n  readonly passes: string[];\n  readonly calls: never[];   // placeholder — no call types yet\n  readonly openedAt: number;\n}\n```\n\n`calls` is typed as `never[]` — it holds no data yet, reserved for future pung/kong/quint actions.\n\n**`PassCallAction`** is the only call-related game action. It is handled in:\n\n**File:** `/Users/rchoi/Personal/mahjong-game/packages/shared/src/engine/actions/call-window.ts`\n\n- `handlePassCall(state, action)` — validates phase/window/discarder/duplicates, records the pass, auto-closes when all 4 players have passed.\n- `closeCallWindow(state, reason)` — clears `callWindow`, handles wall-empty → wall game, advances `currentTurn` counterclockwise to the next seat.\n\nThe discard handler (`discard.ts`) is what opens the call window: it auto-adds the discarder to `passes`, sets `turnPhase = \"callWindow\"`, and populates `callWindow`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Game Engine Reducer\n\n**File:** `/Users/rchoi/Personal/mahjong-game/packages/shared/src/engine/game-engine.ts`\n\n```ts\nexport function handleAction(state: GameState, action: GameAction): ActionResult {\n  switch (action.type) {\n    case \"START_GAME\":   return handleStartGame(state, action);\n    case \"DRAW_TILE\":    return handleDrawTile(state, action);\n    case \"DISCARD_TILE\": return handleDiscardTile(state, action);\n    case \"PASS_CALL\":    return handlePassCall(state, action);\n    default: {\n      const _exhaustive: never = action;\n      return { accepted: false, reason: `UNKNOWN_ACTION: ${(_exhaustive as GameAction).type}` };\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nKey design patterns:\n- **Validate-then-mutate**: handlers return early with `{ accepted: false, reason }` before any mutation; mutations only happen once all validation passes.\n- State is mutated **in-place** (not immutable/cloned).\n- The `default` branch uses an exhaustive `never` check to catch unhandled action types at compile time.\n- `createLobbyState()` produces the initial blank state.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Test Helpers\n\n**File:** `/Users/rchoi/Personal/mahjong-game/packages/shared/src/testing/helpers.ts`\n\n```ts\nexport function createTestState(overrides?: Partial<GameState>, seed: number = 42): GameState {\n  const state = createGame([\"p1\", \"p2\", \"p3\", \"p4\"], seed);\n  if (overrides) {\n    return { ...state, ...overrides };\n  }\n  return state;\n}\n```\n\n- Calls `createGame([\"p1\",\"p2\",\"p3\",\"p4\"], seed)` under the hood.\n- Accepts optional `Partial<GameState>` overrides applied via shallow spread.\n- Default seed is `42` for determinism.\n- Also exports `buildHand(tileIds)` (looks up tiles by ID from the full tile set) and `getPlayerBySeat(state, seat)`.\n\n**File:** `/Users/rchoi/Personal/mahjong-game/packages/shared/src/testing/fixtures.ts`\n\n```ts\nexport const TEST_PLAYER_IDS = [\"p1\", \"p2\", \"p3\", \"p4\"] as const;\nexport const TEST_SEED = 42;\nexport function createLobbyFixture(): GameState { return createLobbyState(); }\nexport function createPlayState(seed: number = TEST_SEED): GameState {\n  return createGame([...TEST_PLAYER_IDS], seed);\n}\n```\n\n`createPlayState()` is the primary fixture used in all call-window tests.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Call Window Implementation (Story 3a-1)\n\nThe story 3a-1 call window is fully implemented and tested.\n\n**Implementation files:**\n- `/Users/rchoi/Personal/mahjong-game/packages/shared/src/engine/actions/discard.ts` — opens the call window on every discard\n- `/Users/rchoi/Personal/mahjong-game/packages/shared/src/engine/actions/call-window.ts` — `handlePassCall` and `closeCallWindow`\n\n**Test file:** `/Users/rchoi/Personal/mahjong-game/packages/shared/src/engine/actions/call-window.test.ts`\n\nTest coverage includes:\n- Discard opens call window with correct shape (status, discardedTile, discarderId, openedAt, empty calls)\n- Discarder is auto-added to `passes` immediately\n- `currentTurn` stays with discarder while window is open (`turnPhase = \"callWindow\"`)\n- `DISCARDER_CANNOT_CALL`, `ALREADY_PASSED`, `NO_CALL_WINDOW`, `WRONG_PHASE` validation rejections\n- Partial passes (1-of-3, 2-of-3) keep window open\n- All-pass (3 non-discarders) triggers `closeCallWindow` → `CALL_WINDOW_CLOSED { reason: \"all_passed\" }`, advances turn counterclockwise (East → South → West → North)\n- `closeCallWindow(\"timer_expired\")` path also tested\n- Wall-empty at close → `gamePhase = \"scoreboard\"`, `gameResult = { winnerId: null, points: 0 }`, resolved `WALL_GAME`\n\n**Constants** (`/Users/rchoi/Personal/mahjong-game/packages/shared/src/constants.ts`):\n`DEFAULT_CALL_WINDOW_MS`, `MIN_CALL_WINDOW_MS`, `MAX_CALL_WINDOW_MS` are exported (timer values for future enforcement)."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e018b2a0-f3f1-40e1-98cc-69fb37f4a59e","uuid":"c0e80aa3-5eda-4f0b-a81d-02e9b7bd5be4","timestamp":"2026-03-28T03:09:43.181Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Search the codebase to understand the current state of:\n1. GameAction and ResolvedAction types - find their discriminated union definitions\n2. Any existing call-related code (pung, kong, quint, call window, etc.)\n3. The current game engine reducer and how actions are dispatched\n4. Test helpers like createTestState and how they work\n5. The call window implementation from story 3a-1\n\nSearch in `packages/shared/` primarily. Return the key file paths and relevant code snippets for each area.","agentId":"af582acf7ed01112b","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a complete summary of the current state of the codebase across all five areas.\n\n---\n\n## 1. GameAction and ResolvedAction Types\n\n**File:** `/Users/rchoi/Personal/mahjong-game/packages/shared/src/types/actions.ts`\n\n`GameAction` is a discriminated union of four action interfaces:\n\n```ts\nexport type GameAction = StartGameAction | DrawTileAction | DiscardTileAction | PassCallAction;\n```\n\n- `START_GAME` — `{ playerIds: string[], seed?: number }`\n- `DRAW_TILE` — `{ playerId: string }`\n- `DISCARD_TILE` — `{ playerId: string, tileId: string }`\n- `PASS_CALL` — `{ playerId: string }`\n\n**File:** `/Users/rchoi/Personal/mahjong-game/packages/shared/src/types/game-state.ts` (lines 93–104)\n\n`ResolvedAction` is a discriminated union embedded in `ActionResult`:\n\n```ts\nexport type ResolvedAction =\n  | { readonly type: \"GAME_STARTED\" }\n  | { readonly type: \"DRAW_TILE\"; readonly playerId: string }\n  | { readonly type: \"DISCARD_TILE\"; readonly playerId: string; readonly tileId: string }\n  | { readonly type: \"WALL_GAME\" }\n  | { readonly type: \"CALL_WINDOW_OPENED\"; readonly discarderId: string; readonly discardedTileId: string }\n  | { readonly type: \"CALL_WINDOW_CLOSED\"; readonly reason: \"all_passed\" | \"timer_expired\" }\n  | { readonly type: \"PASS_CALL\"; readonly playerId: string };\n```\n\nNote: `CALL_WINDOW_OPENED` exists as a type variant but is not currently emitted by any handler — the discard handler returns `DISCARD_TILE` and sets `callWindow` as a side effect without emitting a separate resolved event.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Call-Related Code (Pung, Kong, Quint, Call Window)\n\nThere are no pung/kong/quint action handlers yet. Only the call window infrastructure (story 3a-1) exists:\n\n**`CallWindowState` interface** (`game-state.ts`, lines 62–69):\n```ts\nexport interface CallWindowState {\n  readonly status: \"open\";\n  readonly discardedTile: Tile;\n  readonly discarderId: string;\n  readonly passes: string[];\n  readonly calls: never[];   // placeholder — no call types yet\n  readonly openedAt: number;\n}\n```\n\n`calls` is typed as `never[]` — it holds no data yet, reserved for future pung/kong/quint actions.\n\n**`PassCallAction`** is the only call-related game action. It is handled in:\n\n**File:** `/Users/rchoi/Personal/mahjong-game/packages/shared/src/engine/actions/call-window.ts`\n\n- `handlePassCall(state, action)` — validates phase/window/discarder/duplicates, records the pass, auto-closes when all 4 players have passed.\n- `closeCallWindow(state, reason)` — clears `callWindow`, handles wall-empty → wall game, advances `currentTurn` counterclockwise to the next seat.\n\nThe discard handler (`discard.ts`) is what opens the call window: it auto-adds the discarder to `passes`, sets `turnPhase = \"callWindow\"`, and populates `callWindow`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Game Engine Reducer\n\n**File:** `/Users/rchoi/Personal/mahjong-game/packages/shared/src/engine/game-engine.ts`\n\n```ts\nexport function handleAction(state: GameState, action: GameAction): ActionResult {\n  switch (action.type) {\n    case \"START_GAME\":   return handleStartGame(state, action);\n    case \"DRAW_TILE\":    return handleDrawTile(state, action);\n    case \"DISCARD_TILE\": return handleDiscardTile(state, action);\n    case \"PASS_CALL\":    return handlePassCall(state, action);\n    default: {\n      const _exhaustive: never = action;\n      return { accepted: false, reason: `UNKNOWN_ACTION: ${(_exhaustive as GameAction).type}` };\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nKey design patterns:\n- **Validate-then-mutate**: handlers return early with `{ accepted: false, reason }` before any mutation; mutations only happen once all validation passes.\n- State is mutated **in-place** (not immutable/cloned).\n- The `default` branch uses an exhaustive `never` check to catch unhandled action types at compile time.\n- `createLobbyState()` produces the initial blank state.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Test Helpers\n\n**File:** `/Users/rchoi/Personal/mahjong-game/packages/shared/src/testing/helpers.ts`\n\n```ts\nexport function createTestState(overrides?: Partial<GameState>, seed: number = 42): GameState {\n  const state = createGame([\"p1\", \"p2\", \"p3\", \"p4\"], seed);\n  if (overrides) {\n    return { ...state, ...overrides };\n  }\n  return state;\n}\n```\n\n- Calls `createGame([\"p1\",\"p2\",\"p3\",\"p4\"], seed)` under the hood.\n- Accepts optional `Partial<GameState>` overrides applied via shallow spread.\n- Default seed is `42` for determinism.\n- Also exports `buildHand(tileIds)` (looks up tiles by ID from the full tile set) and `getPlayerBySeat(state, seat)`.\n\n**File:** `/Users/rchoi/Personal/mahjong-game/packages/shared/src/testing/fixtures.ts`\n\n```ts\nexport const TEST_PLAYER_IDS = [\"p1\", \"p2\", \"p3\", \"p4\"] as const;\nexport const TEST_SEED = 42;\nexport function createLobbyFixture(): GameState { return createLobbyState(); }\nexport function createPlayState(seed: number = TEST_SEED): GameState {\n  return createGame([...TEST_PLAYER_IDS], seed);\n}\n```\n\n`createPlayState()` is the primary fixture used in all call-window tests.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Call Window Implementation (Story 3a-1)\n\nThe story 3a-1 call window is fully implemented and tested.\n\n**Implementation files:**\n- `/Users/rchoi/Personal/mahjong-game/packages/shared/src/engine/actions/discard.ts` — opens the call window on every discard\n- `/Users/rchoi/Personal/mahjong-game/packages/shared/src/engine/actions/call-window.ts` — `handlePassCall` and `closeCallWindow`\n\n**Test file:** `/Users/rchoi/Personal/mahjong-game/packages/shared/src/engine/actions/call-window.test.ts`\n\nTest coverage includes:\n- Discard opens call window with correct shape (status, discardedTile, discarderId, openedAt, empty calls)\n- Discarder is auto-added to `passes` immediately\n- `currentTurn` stays with discarder while window is open (`turnPhase = \"callWindow\"`)\n- `DISCARDER_CANNOT_CALL`, `ALREADY_PASSED`, `NO_CALL_WINDOW`, `WRONG_PHASE` validation rejections\n- Partial passes (1-of-3, 2-of-3) keep window open\n- All-pass (3 non-discarders) triggers `closeCallWindow` → `CALL_WINDOW_CLOSED { reason: \"all_passed\" }`, advances turn counterclockwise (East → South → West → North)\n- `closeCallWindow(\"timer_expired\")` path also tested\n- Wall-empty at close → `gamePhase = \"scoreboard\"`, `gameResult = { winnerId: null, points: 0 }`, resolved `WALL_GAME`\n\n**Constants** (`/Users/rchoi/Personal/mahjong-game/packages/shared/src/constants.ts`):\n`DEFAULT_CALL_WINDOW_MS`, `MIN_CALL_WINDOW_MS`, `MAX_CALL_WINDOW_MS` are exported (timer values for future enforcement)."}],"totalDurationMs":53788,"totalTokens":25929,"totalToolUseCount":13,"usage":{"input_tokens":1037,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1257,"cache_read_input_tokens":21592,"output_tokens":2043,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1257},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
